{"_id":"1IS2E3D7wyG9CPEL","name":"Icarus' Promise (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Icarus_Promise.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Ring, uncommon (requires attunement)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Legend tells of a young inventor whose greatest passion was to reach the hallowed, gear-filled halls of the Clockwork Nirvana. His work creating a trans-planar shuttle was fraught with danger, leading him to seek help from the tech-priests of Daedalus. In return for a promise of half of the spoils of his exploration, they granted him this blessed ring. Unfortunately his first foray to the outer planes dropped him immediately adjacent to the Clockwork Nirvana's radiant power core and he was never seen again.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Vow.</em></strong> While you wear this ring you have a +1 bonus to all saving throws. When you break your word or lie, the bonus to saving throws is suspended until the next dawn and the ring flares brightly, dealing [[/r 1d6]] fire damage to you as it gains a new crack. If you roll a 6 on this fire damage, the ring shatters completely and is destroyed.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sunkiss.</em></strong> As an action you can cause the ring to detonate. Each creature within 20 feet of you must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 10d6]] fire damage and [[/r 10d6]] radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. You automatically fail this saving throw. After you use this property the ring is destroyed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6","fire"],["10d6","radiant"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"1d6","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[{"_id":"BbL5jpHejMJrzucw","changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.abilities.save","mode":2,"value":"+1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Icarus_Promise.webp","label":"+1 to Saving Throws","origin":"Item.JipHma98xydotmko","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JipHma98xydotmko"}}}
{"_id":"1LO4DMR22pn4dUIj","name":"Blood Minister Syringe","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Blood_Minister_Syringe.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Wondrous item, uncommon</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Made of silver and glass, this peculiar apparatus magically refills with blood each dawn. A small dial around the plunger depicts carved images of beasts. Rotating the dial to each of these beasts changes the hue of the blood: bear, an iridescent black; bull, a sanguine red; cat, a silky purple; eagle, a piercing yellow; fox, an opulent orange; and owl, a midnight blue. Legend says blood from the sacred animal spirits of each of these races was extracted in the crafting of this macabre, performance-enhancing syringe.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As an action, you can select a beast and inject this blood into a willing creature, casting the spell @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.9eOZDBImVKxbeOyZ]{Enhance Ability} on it. The spell does not require concentration when cast in this way.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3SVrW7ihIyBWtGaE"}}}
{"_id":"1VgkWq8PIy28C45C","name":"Ring of Birdseye Maple","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Ring_of_Birdseye_Maple.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Ring, uncommon (optional attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Pale green, eye-like tourmalines have been encapsulated in maple roots sung by seelie fey into pleasing knots and braids.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This ring has 5 charges, and regains [[/r 1d4 + 1]] expended charges daily at dawn. While wearing the ring, whenever you touch a plant or surface made of wood, you can expend 1 charge to cause an eye to grow anywhere along that plant/surface within 60 feet of you. You can see out of the eye, which has @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.10RNSKCH2hTja3DG]{Darkvision} out to 60 feet, for as long as you remain touching the plant/surface. While you look out of the eye, you are blinded with regards to your own senses.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The eye has a Dexterity (Stealth) modifier of +8. It has AC 10 and 5 hit points. Any damage dealt to the eye is transferred back to you as psychic damage.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Optional Attunement: </strong></em>If you attune to the ring, it gains the following property:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Eyesoar: </strong></em>If you stop touching the wood, the eye persists for one hour or until you create a new eye. So long as the eye is within 150 feet of you, you can use an action to look through the eye. While looking through the eye you can, as an action, move the eye up to 30 feet along the wood.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"none","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"object"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":5,"max":"5","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"1WZH73bOSCu1y3pB","name":"Andvaranaut","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Andvaranaut.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Ring, uncommon</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Glowing with tiny motes of pulsing light, this brilliant golden ring is inscribed with runes of wealth and prosperity. Two legends follow this ring. The first tells of humble folk using the ring to lead modest lives free from discomfort and hardship. The second tells of mighty leaders brought low by their own greed. Which is true&mdash;if any&mdash;is anyone&rsquo;s guess.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Andvari&rsquo;s Gift. As a bonus action you can speak the ring&rsquo;s command word&mdash;&ldquo;plunder&rdquo;&mdash;to form a trail of softly glowing golden dust that leads to the nearest source of gold at least 5 gp in value that is not currently carried or worn by a creature. The trail extends out 100 feet from you, growing as you follow it. The trail can&rsquo;t pass through solid objects but will navigate through holes as small as 1 inch in diameter. If all paths to the gold source are blocked by solid objects, the trail ends as close to the gold as possible. The trail disappears immediately if the gold source is destroyed, transported to another plane, or picked up by a creature.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Curse: Andvari&rsquo;s Avarice.</strong></em> If Andvari&rsquo;s Gift is used three times with one 24 hour span, you become attuned to it. If you have no available attunement slots you must choose one uncursed item from which you immediately become unattuned. Upon attuning to the item you develop dragon fever, which can&rsquo;t be cured while the curse persists:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You have disadvantage on all Wisdom saving throws and checks.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You become uncompromisingly greedy, using all your cunning to keep as much treasure for yourself as possible.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As long as you remain cursed, you can&rsquo;t willingly unattune from the ring and any attempt to discard the ring fails. It always returns to your person in a mysterious way, such as appearing in a pocket, on your finger, or braided into your beard. Remove curse or similar magic can end your attunement to the ring, but does not remove the ring&rsquo;s Andvari&rsquo;s Avarice property.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you relinquish the ring to a person who does not know of the ring&rsquo;s curse, and that can speak the command word, your attunement to the ring ends. You can never again regain the ring through any means; events will conspire to keep it from you.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"20d4uOHneuj0Lx5K","name":"Evening Moon (Legendary)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Evening_Moon.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon, legendary (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<p><em>[[/r 1d6]] slashing - finesse, light, thrown (30/90 ft.)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This three-quarter chakram can sustain itself in flight, returning to its wielder after lacerating its target. Equally lethal in both melee and ranged combat, this weapon is favoured by assassins of the astral sea for its ability to create a moving sphere of shadow, aiding its wielder to slip through enemy lines unseen, even in broad daylight.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon grants a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it, and it returns to your hand immediately after it is used to make a ranged attack. When you hit a creature with the shapechanger tag with this weapon, the creature must succeed on a DC 17 Constitution saving throw or instantly revert to its original form and be unable to assume a different form for the next minute.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Dusk.</em></strong> While you hold this item you can, as an action, create a 20-foot sphere centred on you in which all light becomes dim. This sphere lasts for 8 hours, or until you dismiss it as a bonus action, and it follows you when you move. While Dusk is active, you can hide when only lightly obscured, and you can take the Hide action as a bonus action.</p>\n<p><strong><em>New Moon.</em></strong> After you use the Dusk property, but before the next dusk, you can use an action to cast the invisibility spell on yourself. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following Dusk.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2>Eclipse, Set of the Moon and Stars</h2>\n<p>When the magics of morning star and <em>evening moon</em> become intertwined through attunement to a single wielder, their innate dunmantic magics coalesce creating a miniature solar system.</p>\n<p>While you are attuned to both morning star and <em>evening moon</em>, both items gain an additional +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, the saving throw DCs of both items are increased by 1 , and you can use the Orbit and Eclipse properties.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Orbit.</em></strong> Whenever you make a ranged attack with <em>evening moon</em> while also holding morning star, you can use a bonus action to cause it to begin orbiting you. As part of this bonus action and as a bonus action on subsequent turns, you can make one attack with <em>evening moon</em> against any creature within 15 feet of you.</p>\n<p><em>Evening moon</em> orbits you at a distance of [[/r 1d3]] feet. Any creature within 5 feet of you can use its action to make a DC 21 Dexterity (Acrobatics) check in an attempt to catch <em>evening moon</em>. On a success, the creature catches <em>evening moon</em>. On a failure, it takes [[/r 1d6]] slashing damage.</p>\n<p>While the Orbit property is active, a creature that targets you with a melee attack must succeed on a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d6]] slashing damage immediately before it makes its attack roll.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Eclipse.</em></strong> As a bonus action while <em>evening moon</em> is orbiting you, you can cause it to hover in front of you, casting you in a dark obscuring light. For the next minute you are under the effects of the blur spell. After you activate this effect, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn or dusk.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Thrown.</em></strong> If a weapon has the thrown property, you can throw the weapon to make a ranged attack. If the weapon is a melee weapon, you use the same ability modifier for that attack roll and damage roll that you would use for a melee attack with the weapon. For example, if you throw a handaxe, you use your Strength, but if you throw a dagger, you can use either your Strength or your Dexterity, since the dagger has the finesse property.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":90,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+3","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+3+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"thr":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"26AjZGswtQFbCAnX","name":"Garlycanthrope","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Garlycanthrope.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncomm</em><em>o</em><em>n</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Originally commissioned by an infamous vampire huntress, Dr. Francis N. Stein’s <em>garlycanthrope</em>s have proved themselves the ‘must have commodity’ of the season for monsters hunters everywhere. Their ability to detect undead and shapechangers has saved many potential victims from the jaws of a mimic, or from walking into a vampire’s lair.</p>\n<p>At your command, this inanimate bulb of garlic comes to life, sprouting little legs, eyes, and a panting muzzle for one hour, and gaining the stats and features in the @Compendium[magic-items-vol0-free-for-all.bestiary-vol0-free-for-all.cCl2HrHtqN3pIQ8G]{associated statblock}. It is extremely friendly to you and your friends, but is skittish if any of them are undead or shapechangers.</p>\n<p>It has the unique abilities to smell shapechangers and see undead, even through magical darkness. When you turn from hunter to hunted, it can release a puff of dust hindering your pursuer’s ability to track you, aiding your escape or attempts to hide.</p>\n<p>In combat, the <em>garlycanthrope</em> shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It can move and use its reaction on its own, but the only action it takes on its turn is the Dodge action, unless you take a bonus action on your turn to command it to take one of the actions in its stat block or the Dash, Disengage, Help, Hide or Search action.</p>\n<p>Once you activate the <em>garlycanthrope</em>, you can’t do so again until you finish a long rest. Be careful not to eat it in the meantime!</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2foIyuUfvpayu36D","name":"Gullinbursti Tusks (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Gullinbursti_Tusks.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Simple weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger}), melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement)</em><br />1 lb.<br />[[/r 1d4]] piercing - finesse, light, thrown (20/60 ft.)</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These rough, gold-and-ivory daggers are said to have been forged using leftover materials from the forging of Gullinbursti, the great Golden boar. A restless aura suffuses these blades, from its golden-haired hilt to its ivory points. Attuning to both daggers requires a single attunement slot. While wielding both daggers you can use the <em>Boar&rsquo;s Charge</em> and <em>Spirit of the Golden Boar</em> properties.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><em>Boar&rsquo;s Charge. </em></strong>If you move at least 20 feet straight towards a creature and then hit it with an attack using the tusk the same turn, the target takes an additional [[/r 2d6]] piercing damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a DC 13 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Spirit of the Golden Boar. </em></strong>You call forth Gullinbursti&rsquo;s residual power. As an action, you speak the command word and point your daggers at a point you can see within 30 feet of you. A spectral golden boar charges in a straight line from you to the point. All creatures along this line must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 3d6]] radiant damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":2,"weight":1,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"enemy"},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"mgc":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2shuiiNlowQsJ41U","name":"Morning Star (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Morning_Star.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.dX8AxCh9o0A9CkT3]{Morningstar}), rare (requires attunement)  </em><br /><em>4 lb.</em><br /><em>[[/r 1d8]] piercing</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Within these four, free-floating, ever-moving, gyroscopic rings is contained the source of <em>morning star</em>'s power: a ball of fusion; a miniaturised star. A creature attuned to the item can induce tiny solar flares that can blind or burn those in its path.</p>\n<p>You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Dawn.</em></strong> As an action you can cause <em>morning star</em> to shine a gloriously bright light at all creatures within a 20-foot cone. Each creature in the area must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.995mfaI3z7WtY7vK]{Blinded} until the end of your next turn. One you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Ultraviolet.</em></strong> After you use the Dawn property, but before the next dawn, you can use an action to cause <em>morning star</em> to shine a focussed beam of ultraviolet light in a 5-foot-wide, 50-foot-long line. Each creature in the area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 8d6]] radiant damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until you activate Dawn again.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Eclipse, Set of the Moon and Stars</h2>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\">When the magics of morning star and <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> become intertwined through attunement to a single wielder, their innate dunmantic magics coalesce creating a miniature solar system.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\">While you are attuned to both morning star and <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>, both items gain an additional +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, the saving throw DCs of both items are increased by 1 , and you can use the Orbit and Eclipse properties.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Orbit.</span></strong> Whenever you make a ranged attack with <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> while also holding morning star, you can use a bonus action to cause it to begin orbiting you. As part of this bonus action and as a bonus action on subsequent turns, you can make one attack with <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> against any creature within 15 feet of you.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Evening moon</span> orbits you at a distance of [[/r 1d3]] feet. Any creature within 5 feet of you can use its action to make a DC 21 Dexterity (Acrobatics) check in an attempt to catch <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>. On a success, the creature catches <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>. On a failure, it takes [[/r 1d6]] slashing damage.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eclipse.</span></strong> As a bonus action while <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> is orbiting you, you can cause it to hover in front of you, casting you in a dark obscuring light. For the next minute you are under the effects of the blur spell. You must concentrate on Eclipse as if you were concentrating on a spell. After you activate this effect, you can’t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+1+@mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"32FTxBJSDLIqFuLT","name":"Bow of Bows (Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Bow_of_Bows.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p>Made of springback candy cane and ruby red ribbon, the bow of bows has the unique ability to fire lengths of ribbon up to 60 feet long in lieu of an arrow. This ribbon can be used to pull creatures off balance, as a grappling hook, or to wrap up a foe. Once per turn, you can replace one attack using the bow with one of the following effects:</p>\n<p><strong><em>Yank.</em></strong> Choose a Large or smaller creature within 90 feet. It must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or be pulled and spun up to 15 feet closer to you and become dizzy until the end of its next turn. A dizzy creature&rsquo;s movement is halved and it makes Dexterity checks and saving throws with disadvantage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Wrapped Up.</em></strong> You fire a length of ribbon at a Huge or smaller creature within 90 feet. The creature must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.b4UvTt9P3As79cwm]{Grappled} (escape DC 15). While grappled in this way, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained}. Once you use this feature you can&rsquo;t use any of the Yank or Wrapped Up features again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.3cymOVja8jXbzrdT]{Longbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.oXLCNi1mxo3bITo8]{Bow of Bows (Longbow) (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.GJv6WkD7D2J6rP6M]{Shortbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.zEnJ6ltydtbgsgeR]{Bow of Bows (Shortbow) (Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"35HjmLgJnwQ57I8m","name":"Peppermint Slice (Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sugar_Shivs.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This striped, red blade is enchanted with the power of the elemental peppermint. You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Glaze.</em></strong> As an action you can invoke the weapon, coating you in a thin layer of hard, resistant icing as you cast @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.lCpbSDnLCrrtOB0b]{Peppermint Plate} at 3rd level. Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Magic Item Set.</em></strong> Attuning to both this weapon and the coolmint slice requires only a single attunement slot. If you hit a creature with both of these weapons on the same turn, the weapons become empowered until the end of your next turn. This weapon deals an additional [[/r 1d6]] fire damage and the coolmint slice deals an additional [[/r 1d6]] cold damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.AKV8GIjgGzTWeoJp]{Peppermint Slice (Dagger) (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.JR6yPD3UjjYTE7sE]{Peppermint Slice (Scimitar) (Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"3SSZww8k95YibYXo","name":"Purple Wyrmfist (Legendary)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Purple_Wyrmfist.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>From the striking violet chitin of the subterranean purple worm is crafted this surprisingly tactile gauntlet. Each day, the gauntlet produces a diluted version of the worm's toxin that is able to cause debilitating pain through a single touch. Purple worm chitin is a sound enhancer, able to amplify vibrations and grant its wearer the ability to detect the slightest tremor.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Purple Poison.</em></strong> As a bonus action you can cause the gauntlet to secrete a purple worm toxin. The next time you hit a creature with an unarmed strike, or successfully grapple a creature, the creature must make a DC 17 Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 10d6]] poison damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. After you activate this property, roll a [[/r d10]]. On a 1 or 2 you can't activate this property again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Tactile Touch.</em></strong> As an action you can touch the ground with this gauntlet and gain @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.MzNASNCgB0Qi2m8p]{Tremorsense} out to a radius of 90 feet for as long as you remain in contact with the ground.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":"you successfully hit or grapple a creature with an unarmed strike"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6","poison"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4J3ubF8nVFtDHLI2","name":"Flail of the Elder Deacon (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Flail_of_the_Elder_Deacon.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.UrH3sMdnUDckIHJ6]{Flail}), melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This solid steel incense dispenser dangles at the end of a black metal chain. The heady perfume of incense and myrrh follow in the wake of the bearer of this weighty, magical weapon.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon, which has 3 charges. To recharge the flail, you must perform a one-hour ritual between dawn and dusk, consuming quality incense with a value in gold pieces equal to three times the number of charges you wish to regain.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As an action you can cast the following spells (save DC 13), expending at least the number of charges indicated and requiring no material components. For each additional charge expended above the number indicated, the slot level of the cast spell increases by one.</p>\n<p></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} - 1 charge</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.wqfAVANuQonNBgnL]{Misty Step} - 2 charges</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.TwlD4PLcltv7Xh7j]{Stinking Cloud} - 3 charges</p>\n</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod+2","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jSmOwp3BKW7Kp2iX"}}}
{"_id":"4h5HbfD7peAKa4gM","name":"Peppermint Slice (Very Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sugar_Shivs.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, very rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This striped, red blade is enchanted with the power of the elemental peppermint. You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Glaze.</em></strong> As an action you can invoke the weapon, coating you in a thin layer of hard, resistant icing as you cast @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.lCpbSDnLCrrtOB0b]{Peppermint Plate} at 5th level. Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Magic Item Set.</em></strong> Attuning to both this weapon and the coolmint slice requires only a single attunement slot. If you hit a creature with both of these weapons on the same turn, the weapons become empowered until the end of your next turn. This weapon deals an additional [[/r 1d8]] fire damage and the coolmint slice deals an additional [[/r 1d8]] cold damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.TLPPxIGTFvM7dHmG]{Peppermint Slice (Dagger) (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.A0YAZCTAfTxghD3W]{Peppermint Slice (Scimitar) (Very Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"58mdeqeJazYTmkGr","name":"Phantom Blade Rapier","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantomblade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Martial weapon, melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement) <br />2 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Branton bodged this project up so badly he actually managed to kill the sword. \"Swords aren't even alive\", I hear you say. You're right, they're not. Branton Quark's control of magic is so porous that he not only managed to grant an inanimate object life but, while it was revelling in its new-found consciousness, kill it again almost immediately. The sword is now pissed and haunts any who takes the life of a sentient being. This blade is an almost permanent fixture in the FBI evidence lockers; no-one is quite sure if sword murder is actually an offence.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon deals an extra [[/r 1d4]] psychic damage to any target it hits. This damage is doubled against ethereal targets, such as ghosts and shadows.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Poltergeist.</em></strong> Whenever you kill a non-ethereal creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or more, the phantom blade—or Kaspa as it calls itself—haunts you. You must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or develop one short-term madness effect.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sentience.</em></strong> Kaspa the phantom blade is a sentient, lawful neutral item with an Intelligence of 14, a Wisdom of 12, and a Charisma of 12. It has hearing and</p>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","piercing"],["1d4","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"phantom%20blade%20rapier_lootavern","propDroppable":"item"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.a.kzqrTKXunj5cJDL7"}}}
{"_id":"5cyDhYvjJZGnPG8k","name":"Kobold Wristbow","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Kobold_Wristbow.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.qaSro7kFhxD6INbZ]{Hand Crossbow}), common (requires attunement) <br />Martial weapon, ranged weapon <br />3 lb.<br />[[/r 1d6]] piercing - ammunition (30/120 ft.), light, loading</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Something about this cobbled-together, wrist-mounted, bow-like contraption looks wrong. It shouldn't hold together.There's nothing even holding the string in place. It must be magic. There's no writing on it but, if there was, you feel it'd be written \"Kobbold RystBo\".</p>\n<p><strong><em>Handsfree.</em></strong> The <em>kobold wristbow</em> does not require a free hand to hold or fire.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Quickshot.</em></strong> In response to your mental command, you can release the bow string and make a ranged weapon attack with the loaded wristbow as a bonus action. You must reload a wristbow before firing again.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Reload.</em></strong> You can reload the <em>kobold wristbow</em> using either a bonus action or an action. <span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">This requires at least 1 free hand.</span></p>\n<p><strong><em>Ammunition.</em></strong> You can use a weapon that has the ammunition property to make a ranged attack only if you have ammunition to fire from the weapon. Each time you attack with the weapon, you expend one piece of ammunition. Drawing the ammunition from a quiver, case, or other container is part of the attack. Loading a one-handed weapon requires a free hand. At the end of the battle, you can recover half your expended ammunition by taking a minute to search the battlefield.</p>\n<p>If you use a weapon that has the ammunition property to make a melee attack, you treat the weapon as an improvised weapon. A sling must be loaded to deal any damage when used in this way.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Loading.</em></strong> Because of the time required to load this weapon, you can fire only one piece of ammunition from it when you use an action, bonus action, or reaction to fire it, regardless of the number of attacks you can normally make.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"common","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":120,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"ammo","target":"","amount":1},"ability":"dex","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"lgt":true,"lod":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"62GiiHRYBCfOchQQ","name":"Trident of the Electric Eel (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Trident_of_the_Electric_Eel.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.F65ANO66ckP8FDMa]{Trident}), melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement)</em><br />4 lb.<br />[[/r 1d6]] piercing - thrown (20/60 ft.), versatile ([[/r 1d8]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Imbued with the natural lightning-based magic of the eelfolk, this brass-headed, magical trident is enchanted never to succumb to the corrosive nature of the briny sea.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><em>Discharge.</em></strong> When you make a melee or ranged attack using this magic weapon you can speak its command word as a bonus action, causing it to emit a burst of lightning. Each creature within 5 feet of it (or within 10 feet of it underwater), must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d6]] lightning damage. A creature that fails this saving throw by 10 or more (DC 3) is also stunned until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Dinglehopper.</strong></em> As an action, you can command this weapon to magically shrink down to the size of common oyster folk, known as a dinglehopper, or to re-enlarge.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Lightning.</strong></em> As an action, you can cast the spell @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IyikgTEOTv701jgQ]{Lightning Bolt} (save DC 13). Once you do so, you can&rsquo;t use the Discharge or Lightning feature again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":true,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":null,"path":"itemss","color":"#ae8989"}}}
{"_id":"6dFQXKVcvYgxiGJv","name":"Gullinbursti Tusks (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Gullinbursti_Tusks.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Simple weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger}), melee weapon, rare (requires attunement)</em><br />1 lb.<br />[[/r 1d4]] piercing - finesse, light, thrown (20/60 ft.)</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These rough, gold-and-ivory daggers are said to have been forged using leftover materials from the forging of Gullinbursti, the great Golden boar. A restless aura suffuses these blades, from its golden-haired hilt to its ivory points. Attuning to both daggers requires a single attunement slot. While wielding both daggers you can use the <em>Boar&rsquo;s Charge</em> and <em>Spirit of the Golden Boar</em> properties.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with these weapons.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><em>Boar&rsquo;s Charge. </em></strong>If you move at least 20 feet straight towards a creature and then hit it with an attack using the tusk the same turn, the target takes an additional [[/r 3d6]] piercing damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Spirit of the Golden Boar. </em></strong>You call forth Gullinbursti&rsquo;s residual power. As an action, you speak the command word and point your daggers at a point you can see within 30 feet of you. A spectral golden boar charges in a straight line from you to the point. All creatures along this line must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 6d6]] radiant damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":2,"weight":1,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"enemy"},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod + 1","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"mgc":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"72f4Qv8vjo6Ko090","name":"Wings of Prey (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Wings_of_Prey_Dark.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attuneme</em><em>nt)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Bestowed upon defenders of city walls and mountain rangers alike, these wings bestow great mobility, as well as packing a secret weapon. The appearance of the wings varies from individual to another, shifting in colour to mirror their soul.</p>\n<p>This item has 6 charges and recharges fully at dawn. While attuned to the wings, you have a flying speed equal to 5 multiplied by the number of remaining charges in feet. As a bonus action, you can speak the command word to make the wings appear or disappear.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Razor Sharp.</em></strong> As an action while the wings are present, you can expend 1 charge to hurl a flurry of razor-sharp feathers in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 6d6]] slashing damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":6,"max":"6","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d6","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"782i6wQipeeU6tls","name":"Glaive of the Green Tyrant (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glaive_of_the_Green_Tyrant.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.rOG1OM2ihgPjOvFW]{Glaive}), melee weapon, very rare (requires attunement)</em> <br />6 lb.<br />[[/r 1d10]] slashing - heavy, reach, two-handed</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Legend tells of a great warrior queen who, having bested a bronze dragon in a game of wits, sought the ability to wield the power of storms. With this power, she laid waste to entire armies, throwing them back into the ranks of their allies, or burning them with flashes of incandescent lightning. Some called her liberator, others: tyrant. Though defeated by the Hero in Red, some of her power yet remains in the Green Tyrant's ancient glaive.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Summon Storm.</em></strong> With a flourish of the glaive you can expend a bonus action to whip up a tornado - 5-foot-diameter, 30-foot-high cylinder of rushing air and crackling lightning - centred on a point within 60 feet. The tornado lasts for 1 minute. Each creature that starts its turn in the tornado's space or enters the space for the first time on a turn must make a DC 16 Strength saving throw. On a failure, a creature is thrown 10 feet in a random direction, landing prone, and takes [[/r 1d8]] bludgeoning and [[/r 1d8]] lightning damage. Roll a [[/r d8]] to determine the direction: 1, north; 2, northeast; 3, east; 4, southeast; 5, south; 6, southwest; 7, west; or 8 northwest.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action on your turn while the tornado is conjured, you can move the tornado up to 20 feet. Each creature whose space the tornado moves through must succeed on a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d8]] lightning damage. A creature can't take damage from this effect more than once per turn.</p>\n<p>Once you use the Summon Storm property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Heavy.</em></strong> Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Reach.</em></strong> This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Two-Handed.</em></strong> This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"hvy":true,"rch":true,"two":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"glaive%20of%20the%20green%20tyrant%20(very%20rare)_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Glaive of the Green Tyrant (Very Rare)","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"fluff":{"images":[{"type":"image","href":{"type":"external","url":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glaive_of_the_Green_Tyrant.we