his property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it."]}],"_typeListText":["martial weapon","melee weapon"],"_typeHtml":"martial weapon (glaive), melee weapon","_attunement":"(requires attunement)","_attunementCategory":"Requires Attunement","_fProperties":["heavy","reach","two-handed"],"_fMisc":["Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBaseItem":["glaive|phb"],"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Martial weapon, melee weapon"}}}}}
{"_id":"AVU5ekk4VUCc4FAH","name":"Coralborn Ring","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Coralborn_Ring.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Ring, uncommon</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This coralborn-crafted trinket is often gifted to visiting dignitaries to protect them during journeys through the abrasive subterranean coral tunnels. While wearing this ring, you can spend an action to speak the ring&rsquo;s command word, casting the spell @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.mCCHidqNZY99hQ8o]{Coralskin} on yourself&nbsp;(+3 spellcasting ability modifier). Once you do so, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.83hqDPOppfLTF4kt"}}}
{"_id":"ClUiTAZI6Kmegjey","name":"Phantom Blade Shortsword","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantomblade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Martial weapon, melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement) <br />2 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Branton bodged this project up so badly he actually managed to kill the sword. \"Swords aren't even alive\", I hear you say. You're right, they're not. Branton Quark's control of magic is so porous that he not only managed to grant an inanimate object life but, while it was revelling in its new-found consciousness, kill it again almost immediately. The sword is now pissed and haunts any who takes the life of a sentient being. This blade is an almost permanent fixture in the FBI evidence lockers; no-one is quite sure if sword murder is actually an offence.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon deals an extra [[/r 1d4]] psychic damage to any target it hits. This damage is doubled against ethereal targets, such as ghosts and shadows.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Poltergeist.</em></strong> Whenever you kill a non-ethereal creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or more, the phantom blade—or Kaspa as it calls itself—haunts you. You must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or develop one short-term madness effect.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sentience.</em></strong> Kaspa the phantom blade is a sentient, lawful neutral item with an Intelligence of 14, a Wisdom of 12, and a Charisma of 12. It has hearing and</p>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod","piercing"],["1d4","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"phantom%20blade%20shortsword_lootavern","propDroppable":"item"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.a.9ogMC7SyWWXO0q92"}}}
{"_id":"DGQjRmjv4s4pltCa","name":"Tidecutter (Legendary)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tide_Cutter.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword}), melee weapon, legendary (requires attunement)</em> <br />3 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] slashing - versatile ([[/r 1d10]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p>This item appears to be a sword hilt stylized with tentacles. While grasping the hilt, you can use a bonus action to cause a blade of rushing water to spring forth, or make it disappear. While the blade exists, this magic longsword has the finesse property. If you are proficient with shortswords or longswords, you are proficient with the <em>tidecutter</em>. You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Water Lash.</em></strong> As an action, you can slash the sword towards a target within 30 feet of you, causing the blade to elongate into a lash. Make a melee weapon attack against the target using this weapon&rsquo;s normal statistics. On a hit you can pull a Huge or smaller creature, a Gargauntaun creature if it fails a DC 19 Strength saving throw or an object that weighs 10000 pounds or less, up to 25 feet closer to you. If the target is a fixed object or a Huge or larger creature, you can pull yourself 35 feet towards the target.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Waterborne.</em></strong> When submerged in water, this longsword gains the reach property and the range of the Water Lash feature increases to 40 feet.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Hydrodynamic.</em></strong> Attacking while underwater doesn't impose disadvantage on attack rolls you make with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Versatile.</em></strong> This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the property&mdash;the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+3","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+3+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10+3+@mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ver":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EpnKrr8L5a3x3KUK","name":"Evening Moon (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Evening_Moon.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon, legendary (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<p><em>[[/r 1d6]] slashing - finesse, light, thrown (30/90 ft.)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This three-quarter chakram can sustain itself in flight, returning to its wielder after lacerating its target. Equally lethal in both melee and ranged combat, this weapon is favoured by assassins of the astral sea for its ability to create a moving sphere of shadow, aiding its wielder to slip through enemy lines unseen, even in broad daylight.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon grants a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it, and it returns to your hand immediately after it is used to make a ranged attack. When you hit a creature with the shapechanger tag with this weapon, the creature must succeed on a DC 16 Constitution saving throw or instantly revert to its original form and be unable to assume a different form for the next minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Dusk. </strong>While you hold this item you can, as an action, create a 20-foot sphere centred on you in which all light becomes dim. This sphere lasts for 8 hours, or until you dismiss it as a bonus action, and it follows you when you move. While Dusk is active, you can hide when only lightly obscured, and you can take the Hide action as a bonus action. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dusk.</p>\n<p><strong>New Moon. </strong>After you use the Dusk property, but before the next dusk, you can use an action to cast the invisibility spell on yourself. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following Dusk.</p>\n<p><strong>Finesse. </strong>When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong>Light. </strong>A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>\n<p><strong>Thrown. </strong>If a weapon has the thrown property, you can throw the weapon to make a ranged attack. If the weapon is a melee weapon, you use the same ability modifier for that attack roll and damage roll that you would use for a melee attack with the weapon. For example, if you throw a handaxe, you use your Strength, but if you throw a dagger, you can use either your Strength or your Dexterity, since the dagger has the finesse property.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":90,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+2+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"thr":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Fva7xtf6m9GovKCK","name":"Magehunter Blade (Very Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Blade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Generic variant, very rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Made of a weave-intersecting alloy, these armaments were the go-to weapon for the mage-hunting Order of the Spellbreakers. Fanatical elements within the order have recently taken power, bringing with them an abhorrence for all things magical. Having largely destroyed this magical cache, such weapons are now very rare and are only wielded by the few who cling to the old ways.</p>\n<p>You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. If you hit a target that is under the effect of a spell or magical effect, the spell is dispelled if it is 5th-level or lower, and the target takes an additional [[/r 1d8]] force damage for each level of the dispelled spell (dispelled cantrips deal no additional damage). Once a spell is dispelled, roll a [[/r d6]]. If the number is equal to or lower than the level of the dispelled spell, the blade loses this feature until the following dawn.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.xMkP8BmFzElcsMaR]{Greatsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.cfXJ4zE5KZPx31ao]{Magehunter Greatsword (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.ABBjB1Vl1NKauyoe]{Magehunter Longsword (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.QSWVi2An2ohTKfjn]{Magehunter Rapier (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.22IKJsfK47feInE1]{Magehunter Scimitar (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.osLzOwQdPtrK3rQH]{Shortsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.WkTcGDROVrI0xfYw]{Magehunter Shortsword (Very Rare)})</li>\n</ul>\n\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"G2WV73s4ZOytNOnf","name":"Phantom Blade Scimitar","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantomblade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Martial weapon, melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement) <br />3 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Branton bodged this project up so badly he actually managed to kill the sword. \"Swords aren't even alive\", I hear you say. You're right, they're not. Branton Quark's control of magic is so porous that he not only managed to grant an inanimate object life but, while it was revelling in its new-found consciousness, kill it again almost immediately. The sword is now pissed and haunts any who takes the life of a sentient being. This blade is an almost permanent fixture in the FBI evidence lockers; no-one is quite sure if sword murder is actually an offence.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon deals an extra [[/r 1d4]] psychic damage to any target it hits. This damage is doubled against ethereal targets, such as ghosts and shadows.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Poltergeist.</em></strong> Whenever you kill a non-ethereal creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or more, the phantom blade—or Kaspa as it calls itself—haunts you. You must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or develop one short-term madness effect.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sentience.</em></strong> Kaspa the phantom blade is a sentient, lawful neutral item with an Intelligence of 14, a Wisdom of 12, and a Charisma of 12. It has hearing and</p>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod","slashing"],["1d4","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"phantom%20blade%20scimitar_lootavern","propDroppable":"item"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.a.8u0HnYBxb2bZlWH8"}}}
{"_id":"GQeYLQKWeXkb5Arv","name":"Tome of Living Memories (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tome_of_Living_Memories3.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Wondrous item, very rare (optional attunement by a wizard)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>The pages of this book are littered with the shifting memories of all the aboleth broodmother's eyes have seen. This deluge of information includes historical occurrences, the gods, and all things arcane, in addition to several spells. Unfortunately, the script is a shifting mire of letters that only the most astute can decipher.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Knowledge from Beyond.</em></strong> Over the course of a minute, you can attempt to discern information from the broodmother's memories. Make a DC 10 Intelligence check. On a success, you gain proficiency in Arcana, History, Nature, and Religion for the next 10 minutes. On a failure, you take psychic damage equal to your level.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Shrouded Spells.</em></strong> In a similar manner, you can spend 10 minutes attempting to cast one of the following spells, requiring no material components and without expending a spell slot. At the end of the 10 minutes, make an Intelligence check. The DC equals 8 plus the spell's level. On a success, you cast the spell. On a failure, you don't cast the spell and you take psychic damage equal to twice the spell's level.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.3OZnNhunvRtPOQmH]{Identify} (1st-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.4v2H3hHb3Ph9XLNd]{Augury} (2nd-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.cg50KpBkBdPK6vPL]{Clairvoyance} (3rd-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.XqzXSKNR75ZdYTA9]{Divination} (4th-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.W4Qx5z0id6da0vqg]{Legend Lore} (5th-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.dSTu1MaPhBqPITwM]{Contact Other Plane} (5th-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.cYI4RNNjI5GAmLhy]{Find the Path} (6th-level)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Optional Attunement.</em> <em>Wizard.</em></strong> If you have at least 1 wizard level then you can choose to attune to thismitem. While you remain attuned to it, you can use it as a spellbook and an arcane focus. While you use this tome as your spellbook, the comprehend languages and detect thoughts spells are added to your known spells and you always have them prepared. You can also prepare 2 additional Wizard spells at the end of a long rest and you know the guidance cantrip, which is a wizard spell for you.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":null,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GlTZ3ZQQUJ4bk1Jm","name":"Peppermint Slice (Uncommon)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sugar_Shivs.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This striped, red blade is enchanted with the power of the elemental peppermint. You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Glaze.</em></strong> As an action you can invoke the weapon, coating you in a thin layer of hard, resistant icing as you cast @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.lCpbSDnLCrrtOB0b]{Peppermint Plate}. Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Magic Item Set.</em></strong> Attuning to both this weapon and the coolmint slice requires only a single attunement slot. If you hit a creature with both of these weapons on the same turn, the weapons become empowered until the end of your next turn. This weapon deals an additional [[/r 1d4]] fire damage and the coolmint slice deals an additional [[/r 1d4]] cold damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.J3V5UwQVORpHEvIk]{Peppermint Slice (Dagger) (Uncommon)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.YkfTiYLrtmWhtRXS]{Peppermint Slice (Scimitar) (Uncommon)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GqggEhYHTmgY4BAA","name":"Bow of Bows (Uncommon)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Bow_of_Bows.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Made of springback candy cane and ruby red ribbon, the bow of bows has the unique ability to fire lengths of ribbon up to 60 feet long in lieu of an arrow. This ribbon can be used to pull creatures off balance, as a grappling hook, or to wrap up a foe. Once per turn, you can replace one attack using the bow with one of the following effects:</p>\n<p><strong><em>Yank.</em></strong> Choose a Large or smaller creature within 60 feet. It must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or be pulled and spun up to 15 feet closer to you and become dizzy until the end of its next turn. A dizzy creature&rsquo;s movement is halved and it makes Dexterity checks and saving throws with disadvantage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Wrapped Up.</em></strong> You fire a length of ribbon at a Huge or smaller creature within 60 feet. The creature must succeed on a DC 13 Strength saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.b4UvTt9P3As79cwm]{Grappled} (escape DC 13). While grappled in this way, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained}. Once you use this feature you can&rsquo;t use any of the Yank or Wrapped Up features again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.3cymOVja8jXbzrdT]{Longbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.n702R8BcOt3F8TPv]{Bow of Bows (Longbow) (Uncommon)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.GJv6WkD7D2J6rP6M]{Shortbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.YTkzzK6jg683SSH6]{Bow of Bows (Shortbow) (Uncommon)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"HIxV96hdR3yXv6uA","name":"Glove of the Drider Man","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glove_of_the_Drider_Man.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">When Dr. Stein heard the tales of &lsquo;Driderman, Vigilante of The Low&rsquo;, a humanoid who gained spider-like powers after being bitten by an enchanted drider, he vowed to fabricate items able to recreate Driderman&rsquo;s acrobatic feats. Picosilk, from the miniscule picorachnid spiders, is woven into the world&rsquo;s thinnest, strongest, and most tactile cloth. These lightweight picosilk gloves, worth more than their weight in platinum, are enchanted to fire spiders&rsquo; silk in a variety of formats; as lines, bolts, and whips.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These gloves have 20 charges, and regain [[/r 1d10 + 10]] charges daily at dawn. You can expend charges in the following ways.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Spiderclimb.</strong></em> As an action you can expend a charge to cast the spell @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.KJRVzeMQXPj8Gtyx]{Spider Climb} on yourself with a duration of 1 minute (no concentration required).</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Spiderline.</strong></em> &nbsp;As a reaction when you fall, or as an action, you can expend one charge to produce a 50-foot line of picosilk that can stick to any surface and lasts for 10 minutes, after which it crumbles into dust. It can be used to arrest a fall, climb a wall without a check, or grab an object. Space permitting, if you use this while falling, you can make a DC 15 Dexterity (Acrobatics) check to swing back up. On a successful check you return to the same height from which you fell (or 50 feet, whichever is less). On a failure, you merely stop your fall.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Web Bolt.</strong></em> As an attack when you take the Attack or Ready action, you can expend a charge to make a ranged weapon attack (range 30/120 ft.) against a target. On a hit, the target must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw, becoming @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained} on a failure, or having its speed halved until the end of its next turn on a success. As an action, a creature can make a DC 15 Strength check, freeing A creature @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained} in this way on a success.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":120,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":20,"max":"20","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"On a failed save, the creature is restrained. On a success, their movement speed is halved. The creature can attempt a DC 15 Strength check to free itself as an action.","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"str","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ICjHgTWR9ZEaCq4r","name":"Wings of Prey (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Wings_of_Prey_Light.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attuneme</em><em>nt)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Bestowed upon defenders of city walls and mountain rangers alike, these wings bestow great mobility, as well as packing a secret weapon. The appearance of the wings varies from individual to another, shifting in colour to mirror their soul.</p>\n<p>This item has 3 charges and recharges fully at dawn. While attuned to the wings, you have a flying speed equal to 5 multiplied by the number of remaining charges in feet. As a bonus action, you can speak the command word to make the wings appear or disappear.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Razor Sharp.</em></strong> As an action while the wings are present, you can expend 1 charge to hurl a flurry of razor-sharp feathers in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 4d6]] slashing damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d6","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IMOuivFYAtcCOo0v","name":"Sleuth's Shadowcoat (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sleuths_Shadowcoat.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Sometimes a detective’s best tool is remaining unde - tected. The sleuth’s shadowcoat allows its wearer to take full advantage of shadows, to hide in plain sight, and to disappear in a puff of smoke (well… fog) when things go awry. Also, it has plenty of secret and obvi - ous pockets in which to store things. Very useful.</p>\n<p>This item has 10 charges and regains [[/r 1d6 + 4]] expended charges daily at dawn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Shadow Stealth.</strong></em> While in dim light or darkness, you can expend 1 charge as a bonus action to turn invis - ible until the start of your next turn. If you use your bonus action to spend 1 charge at the start of your next turn, this effect continues without interruption. This invisibility ends if you become brightly lit, or if you attack or cast a spell.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Hide in Plain Sight. </strong></em>As an action, you can spend 2 charges to cast the @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.JShwwDrTzHTvgN7Y]{Chameleon Skin} spell on yourself.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Disappearing Act.</strong></em> As an action, you can expend 2 charges to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} spell centred on yourself, and immediately move up to half your speed. @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} has a duration of Concentration, up to 1 minute, when cast in this way.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":10,"max":"10","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6e7M111QljHz5qbf"}}}
{"_id":"Igwrx2P2EOBppeTy","name":"Heart of Stone (Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Heart_of_Stone.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Spellcasting focus, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>When a fiend dies whilst in close proximity to this fist-sized lump of obsidian, its soul is incarcerated within its inky confines. A creature that attunes to this petrified archdevil's heart learns the name of any soul imprisoned within it and can drain their life force to create powerful magic. However, with each interaction, there is always a chance that the fiend can break free of this crystalline jail.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Soultrap.</em></strong> When a fiend of CR 12 or lower dies within 10 feet of the heart and the heart doesn't already have a soul trapped within it, the fiend's soul becomes trapped within the heart. The heart gains a number of charges equal to the number of hit dice the fiend possesses. If all these charges are used, the soul is shredded and the fiend is destroyed.</p>\n<p>Whenever you hold the stone, you can communicate with the imprisoned soul, if it is willing. You can release an imprisoned soul back to the lower planes as an action.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Soulshred.</em></strong> While you hold the heart, you can expend charges from it to cast the following spells, requiring no material components. If a saving throw is required, the DC is 15.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.95K2aUhAGV9qXjnf]{Bane} (1 charge)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.3MYDjS6k9IYL0aTj]{Calm Emotions} (2 charges)</li>\n<li>enrage (2 charges)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.pO4zGe5LmFIYqJiL]{Bestow Curse} (3 charges)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.XZhdgVK3cLoxNCQl]{Remove Curse} (3 charges)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After you cast a spell using Soulshred, you must make a Charisma check contested by the imprisoned fiend's Charisma check. On a failure, the fiend's soul escapes and is released back to the lower planes and the heart loses all its remaining charges. If a soul escapes while its wielder is on the lower planes, the fiend can immediately materialise.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"heart%20of%20stone%20(rare)_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Heart of Stone (Rare)","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"type":"SCF","fluff":{"images":[{"type":"image","href":{"type":"external","url":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Heart_of_Stone.webp"}}]},"rarity":"rare","reqAttune":true,"entries":["When a fiend dies whilst in close proximity to this fist-sized lump of obsidian, its soul is incarcerated within its inky confines. A creature that attunes to this {@condition petrified} archdevil's heart learns the name of any soul imprisoned within it and can drain their life force to create powerful magic. However, with each interaction, there is always a chance that the fiend can break free of this crystalline jail.",{"type":"entries","name":"Soultrap","entries":["When a fiend of CR 12 or lower dies within 10 feet of the heart and the heart doesn't already have a soul trapped within it, the fiend's soul becomes trapped within the heart. The heart gains a number of charges equal to the number of hit dice the fiend possesses. If all these charges are used, the soul is shredded and the fiend is destroyed.","Whenever you hold the stone, you can communicate with the imprisoned soul, if it is willing. You can release an imprisoned soul back to the lower planes as an action."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Soulshred","entries":["While you hold the heart, you can expend charges from it to cast the following spells, requiring no material components. If a saving throw is required, the DC is 15.","* bane (1 charge)","* calm emotions (2 charges)","* enrage (2 charges)","* bestow curse (3 charges)","* remove curse (3 charges)","After you cast a spell using Soulshred, you must make a Charisma check contested by the imprisoned fiend's Charisma check. On a failure, the fiend's soul escapes and is released back to the lower planes and the heart loses all its remaining charges. If a soul escapes while its wielder is on the lower planes, the fiend can immediately materialise."]}],"uniqueId":"daffd9f9f9ae64eec2e307420b15517a","_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["spellcasting focus"],"_typeHtml":"spellcasting focus","_attunement":"(requires attunement)","_attunementCategory":"Requires Attunement","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["Magic"],"_fFocus":[],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBaseItem":[],"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Spellcasting focus"}}}}}
{"name":"Chameleon Skin","type":"spell","img":"icons/magic/control/silhouette-hold-change-green.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You imbue a creature you touch with pigment so that its skin, and anything it wears or carries, slowly shifts hues to match its surroundings. For the duration, the target can take the Hide action, even when only lightly obscured, as a bonus action on each of its turns.</p>\n<p>If the target did not move during its last turn, creatures have disadvantage on any Wisdom (Perception) checks made to see the target. Creatures who do not rely on sight, such as with tremorsense, are immune to this effect.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Class:</strong> Bard, Druid, Ranger, Wizard</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"red, yellow, and blue pigment","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.haygeiG4GPRWgvlb"}},"_id":"JShwwDrTzHTvgN7Y"}
{"name":"Bracers of the Jaguar Warrior","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Bracers_of_the_Jaguar_Warrior.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>These golden bracers are adorned with three glowing green gems. They are often worn by jaguar warriors tasked to defend the sun god's temple against intruders and wild animals. It is said that the bracers are imbued with the spirits of the jaguar guardians. Layers of fur line the edges of the bracers, offering protection against cuts and stings. While wearing these bracers, you gain a +1 bonus to AC.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Jaguar Spirit Claw.</em></strong> You can use a bonus action to speak this bracer's command word, calling upon the Jaguar spirits. Three radiant claws appear from the gems, granting you the following benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Your unarmed strikes deal radiant damage instead of bludgeoning damage.</li>\n<li>Your unarmed strikes count as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to non magical attacks and damage.</li>\n<li>You can add your Wisdom modifier to your unarmed strike’s damage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The claws last for one minute or until you speak the command word again (no action required). This property can't be used again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>\n\n <p><strong><em>Jaguar Guardian.</em></strong> While you wear these bracers, you can use an action to speak the command word and call forth jaguar spirits to protect you. The spirits prowl around you to a distance of 15 feet for 1 minute or until your concentration ends (as if concentrating on a spell). When you activate this property, you can designate any number of creatures you can see to be unaffected by it. An affected creature’s speed is halved in the area, and when the creature enters the area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a DC15 Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/r 3d8]] radiant damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage. This property can't be used again until you finish a long rest.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"lr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","radiant"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":1,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[{"_id":"beX9nsBvu50QQazI","changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.ac.bonus","mode":2,"value":"+1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Bracers_of_the_Jaguar_Warrior.webp","label":"+1 to AC","origin":"Item.TS9Qwim05bzpSNKe","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.magic-items-vol7-welcome-to-the-jungle.magic-items-vol7-welcome-to-the-jungle.sutrreE1Ffsg4nYs"}},"_id":"JUUUDzEgbbTFOd2s"}
{"_id":"JfYzhtRnksFGLI1b","name":"Magehunter Blade (Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Blade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Generic variant, rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Made of a weave-intersecting alloy, these armaments were the go-to weapon for the mage-hunting Order of the Spellbreakers. Fanatical elements within the order have recently taken power, bringing with them an abhorrence for all things magical. Having largely destroyed this magical cache, such weapons are now very rare and are only wielded by the few who cling to the old ways.</p>\n<p>You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. If you hit a target that is under the effect of a spell or magical effect, the spell is dispelled if it is 3th-level or lower, and the target takes an additional [[/r 1d8]] force damage for each level of the dispelled spell (dispelled cantrips deal no additional damage). Once a spell is dispelled, roll a [[/r d4]]. If the number is equal to or lower than the level of the dispelled spell, the blade loses this feature until the following dawn.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.xMkP8BmFzElcsMaR]{Greatsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.SukrsSwkOKeq39sA]{Magehunter Greatsword (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.3yiCQyCg3L4ypfRk]{Magehunter Longsword (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.L9u2KW8DGzdQQB63]{Magehunter Rapier (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.P1wkkFyHJXgO8I3y]{Magehunter Scimitar (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.osLzOwQdPtrK3rQH]{Shortsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.2adrNgbCgD40vnsT]{Magehunter Shortsword (Rare)})</li>\n</ul>\n\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"JjVZpGoh1SBoCJkt","name":"Coolmint Slice (Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sugar_Shivs.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This striped, blue blade is enchanted with the power of the elemental coolmint. You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Glaze.</em></strong> While holding this weapon, you can use your action to conjure a torrent of sticky, white and purple sugar as you cast the @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.XX2v3qBfUo8vi9oQ]{Cone of Frosting} spell at 3rd level (save DC 15). Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Magic Item Set.</em></strong> Attuning to both this weapon and the peppermint slice requires only a single attunement slot. If you hit a creature with both of these weapons on the same turn, the weapons become empowered until the end of your next turn. This weapon deals an additional [[/r 1d6]] cold damage and the peppermint slice deals an additional [[/r 1d6]] fire damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.HUIW80hYTFqijkhB]{Coolmint Slice (Dagger) (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.mvR7WV6CJ6OAt6Vx]{Coolmint Slice (Scimitar) (Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"LDXHQxoxP3XESBHi","name":"Eyes of the Forgotten (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Eyes_of_the_Forgotten.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Ring, very rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>The barnacle-like yellow eyes that adorn this ring flick to and fro with reptilian suddenness. When you make eye contact with one of them, brief feelings of drowsiness, terror, and nausea wash over you before it darts away once more.</p>\n<p>This ring has <strong>5 charges</strong>, represented by the 5 open eyes. The ring regains <strong>[[/r 1d4 + 1]]</strong> charges daily at midnight. As an action you can expend a charge, thrusting the ring towards a creature you can see within <strong>60 feet</strong> while speaking the command word and causing one of the ring’s eyes to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.ZRqu3Xh9FmlBCZGy]{Eyebite} spell (<strong>save DC 17</strong>) with a duration of <strong>1 minute</strong> (no concentration required).</p>\n<p>For the duration a creature is affected, the eye on the ring becomes an inky void, imbued with dread power. If a save is succeeded, or when the duration elapses, the eye closes.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":5,"max":"5","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Lp9o4EY3JPa4CaOy","name":"Bow of Bows (Very Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Bow_of_Bows.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, very rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p>Made of springback candy cane and ruby red ribbon, the bow of bows has the unique ability to fire lengths of ribbon up to 60 feet long in lieu of an arrow. This ribbon can be used to pull creatures off balance, as a grappling hook, or to wrap up a foe. Once per turn, you can replace one attack using the bow with one of the following effects:</p>\n<p><strong><em>Yank.</em></strong> Choose a Large or smaller creature within 120 feet. It must succeed on a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw or be pulled and spun up to 15 feet closer to you and become dizzy until the end of its next turn. A dizzy creature&rsquo;s movement is halved and it makes Dexterity checks and saving throws with disadvantage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Wrapped Up.</em></strong> You fire a length of ribbon at a Huge or smaller creature within 120 feet. The creature must succeed on a DC 16 Strength saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.b4UvTt9P3As79cwm]{Grappled} (escape DC 13). While grappled in this way, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained}. Once you use this feature you can&rsquo;t use any of the Yank or Wrapped Up features again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.3cymOVja8jXbzrdT]{Longbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.yVxwUY6tIzBgpTCT]{Bow of Bows (Longbow) (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.GJv6WkD7D2J6rP6M]{Shortbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.oeSjUYEzoEaIs0LK]{Bow of Bows (Shortbow) (Very Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"M19FOhwU6EgUmCa7","name":"Heart of Stone (Uncommon)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Heart_of_Stone.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Spellcasting focus, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>When a fiend dies whilst in close proximity to this fist-sized lump of obsidian, its soul is incarcerated within its inky confines. A creature that attunes to this petrified archdevil's heart learns the name of any soul imprisoned within it and can drain their life force to create powerful magic. However, with each interaction, there is always a chance that the fiend can break free of this crystalline jail.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Soultrap.</em></strong> When a fiend of CR 6 or lower dies within 10 feet of the heart and the heart doesn't already have a soul trapped within it, the fiend's soul becomes trapped within the heart. The heart gains a number of charges equal to the number of hit dice the fiend possesses. If all these charges are used, the soul is shredded and the fiend is destroyed.</p>\n<p>Whenever you hold the stone, you can communicate with the imprisoned soul, if it is willing. You can release an imprisoned soul back to the lower planes as an action.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Soulshred.</em></strong> While you hold the heart, you can expend charges from it to cast the following spells, requiring no material components. If a saving throw is required, the DC is 13.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.95K2aUhAGV9qXjnf]{Bane} (1 charge)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.3MYDjS6k9IYL0aTj]{Calm Emotions} (2 charges)</li>\n<li>enrage (2 charges)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After you cast a spell using Soulshred, you must make a Charisma check contested by the imprisoned fiend's Charisma check. On a failure, the fiend's soul escapes and is released back to the lower planes and the heart loses all its remaining charges. If a soul escapes while its wielder is on the lower planes, the fiend can immediately materialise.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"heart%20of%20stone%20(uncommon)_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Heart of Stone (Uncommon)","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"type":"SCF","fluff":{"images":[{"type":"image","href":{"type":"external","url":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Heart_of_Stone.webp"}}]},"rarity":"uncommon","reqAttune":true,"entries":["When a fiend dies whilst in close proximity to this fist-sized lump of obsidian, its soul is incarcerated within its inky confines. A creature that attunes to this {@condition petrified} archdevil's heart learns the name of any soul imprisoned within it and can drain their life force to create powerful magic. However, with each interaction, there is always a chance that the fiend can break free of this crystalline jail.",{"type":"entries","name":"Soultrap","entries":["When a fiend of CR 6 or lower dies within 10 feet of the heart and the heart doesn't already have a soul trapped within it, the fiend's soul becomes trapped within the heart. The heart gains a number of charges equal to the number of hit dice the fiend possesses. If all these charges are used, the soul is shredded and the fiend is destroyed.","Whenever you hold the stone, you can communicate with the imprisoned soul, if it is willing. You can release an imprisoned soul back to the lower planes as an action."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Soulshred","entries":["While you hold the heart, you can expend charges from it to cast the following spells, requiring no material components. If a saving throw is required, the DC is 13.","* bane (1 charge)","* calm emotions (2 charges)","* enrage (2 charges)","After you cast a spell using Soulshred, you must make a Charisma check contested by the imprisoned fiend's Charisma check. On a failure, the fiend's soul escapes and is released back to the lower planes and the heart loses all its remaining charges. If a soul escapes while its wielder is on the lower planes, the fiend can immediately materialise."]}],"uniqueId":"6ee0eb10a1268d65771e11d5946131e7","_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["spellcasting focus"],"_typeHtml":"spellcasting focus","_attunement":"(requires attunement)","_attunementCategory":"Requires Attunement","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["Magic"],"_fFocus":[],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBaseItem":[],"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Spellcasting focus"}}}}}
{"_id":"NU7zp8xf1f4YSCYT","name":"Trident of the Electric Eel (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Trident_of_the_Electric_Eel.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.F65ANO66ckP8FDMa]{Trident}), melee weapon, very rare (requires attunement)</em><br />4 lb.<br />[[/r 1d6]] piercing - thrown (20/60 ft.), versatile ([[/r 1d8]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Imbued with the natural lightning-based magic of the eelfolk, this brass-headed, magical trident is enchanted never to succumb to the corrosive nature of the briny sea.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><em>Discharge.</em></strong> When you make a melee or ranged attack using this magic weapon you can speak its command word as a bonus action, causing it to emit a burst of lightning. Each creature within 5 feet of it (or within 10 feet of it underwater), must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 2d6]] lightning damage. A creature that fails this saving throw by 10 or more (DC 3) is also stunned until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Dinglehopper.</strong></em> As an action, you can command this weapon to magically shrink down to the size of common oyster folk, known as a dinglehopper, or to re-enlarge.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Lightning.</strong></em> As an action, you can cast the spell @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.QbTxN5dWIbYZ4jLU]{Chain Lightning} (save DC 17). Once you do so, you can&rsquo;t use the Discharge or Lightning feature again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":true,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":null,"path":"itemss","color":"#ae8989"}}}
{"_id":"Na5xY3KVj2BT7iTN","name":"Tome of Living Memories (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tome_of_Living_Memories2.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Wondrous item, rare (optional attunement by a wizard)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>The pages of this book are littered with the shifting memories of all the aboleth broodmother's eyes have seen. This deluge of information includes historical occurrences, the gods, and all things arcane, in addition to several spells. Unfortunately, the script is a shifting mire of letters that only the most astute can decipher.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Knowledge from Beyond.</em></strong> Over the course of a minute, you can attempt to discern information from the broodmother's memories. Make a DC 10 Intelligence check. On a success, you gain proficiency in Arcana, History, Nature, and Religion for the next 10 minutes. On a failure, you take psychic damage equal to your level.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Shrouded Spells.</em></strong> In a similar manner, you can spend 10 minutes attempting to cast one of the following spells, requiring no material components and without expending a spell slot. At the end of the 10 minutes, make an Intelligence check. The DC equals 8 plus the spell's level. On a success, you cast the spell. On a failure, you don't cast the spell and you take psychic damage equal to twice the spell's level.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.3OZnNhunvRtPOQmH]{Identify} (1st-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.4v2H3hHb3Ph9XLNd]{Augury} (2nd-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.cg50KpBkBdPK6vPL]{Clairvoyance} (3rd-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.XqzXSKNR75ZdYTA9]{Divination} (4th-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.W4Qx5z0id6da0vqg]{Legend Lore} (5th-level)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Optional Attunement.</em></strong> <em><strong>Wizard.</strong></em> If you have at least 1 wizard level then you can choose to attune to thismitem. While you remain attuned to it, you can use it as a spellbook and an arcane focus. While you use this tome as your spellbook, the comprehend languages and detect thoughts spells are added to your known spells and you always have them prepared. You can also prepare 1 additional Wizard spell at the end of a long rest and you know the guidance cantrip, which is a wizard spell for you.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":null,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Icarus' Promise (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Icarus_Promise.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Ring, very rare (requires attunement)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Legend tells of a young inventor whose greatest passion was to reach the hallowed, gear-filled halls of the Clockwork Nirvana. His work creating a trans-planar shuttle was fraught with danger, leading him to seek help from the tech-priests of Daedalus. In return for a promise of half of the spoils of his exploration, they granted him this blessed ring. Unfortunately his first foray to the outer planes dropped him immediately adjacent to the Clockwork Nirvana's radiant power core and he was never seen again.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Vow.</em></strong> While you wear this ring you have a +2 bonus to all saving throws. When you break your word or lie, the bonus to saving throws is suspended until the next dawn and the ring flares brightly, dealing [[/r 1d10]] fire damage to you as it gains a new crack. If you roll a 10 on this fire damage, the ring shatters completely and is destroyed.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sunkiss.</em></strong> As an action you can cause the ring to detonate. Each creature within 20 feet of you must make a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 20d6]] fire damage and [[/r 20d6]] radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. You automatically fail this saving throw. After you use this property the ring is destroyed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["20d6","fire"],["20d6","radiant"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"1d10","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[{"_id":"zmcoJux3TXf5oxY9","changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.abilities.save","mode":2,"value":"+2","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Icarus_Promise.webp","label":"+2 to Saving Throws","origin":"Item.5RrLZQtmfCNfSwgt","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5RrLZQtmfCNfSwgt"}},"_id":"NwRnCbpZ83SzNlzQ"}
{"_id":"NzuF0ytXUGhso1De","name":"Coralborn Harp (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Coralborn_Harp.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, instrument, rare (requires attunement)</em> <br /><br />2 lb.<br /></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Coralborn have two genres of music; diurnal and nocturnal. The diurnal celebrates the reef&rsquo;s colour, community, and biodiversity; it is often uplifting and joyful. The nocturnal illustrates the hunt, when sharks prowl, and the millions of tiny medusozoa that make up the coral feed. Though this harp can play any type of music, the time of day can accentuate its magical capabilities.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Diurnal Dream.</em></strong> As an action during the day, you can play one of the following tunes, targeting one creature that can hear you within 30 feet, which must make a DC 16 Wisdom saving throw. If the effect ends at the start of your next turn and you immediately use your action at the start of your turn to continue playing the same tune, the effect continues, no saving throw required.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Charming Melody.</em></strong> On a failed save, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.H8aTFVG3YFAkQ3TK]{Charmed}&nbsp;until the start of your next turn. The effect ends early if you or any of your allies harm the creature. When the effect ends, the creature knows it was charmed by you.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Gentle Lullaby.</em></strong> The creature falls @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.MOk1rkF0DeJlcC4l]{Unconscious} until the end of your next turn. A creature that has legs falls @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}&nbsp;when it falls asleep (at the GM&rsquo;s discretion). The effect ends early if the creature takes damage or if someone uses an action to shake the creature awake.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Mesmerising Canon.</em></strong> The creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.tUYvSkhggFcMpVw5]{Incapacitated}&nbsp;until the start of your next turn, using all its movement to follow you. If it is unable to follow the harpist, or if doing so would result in the creature being harmed, it remains motionless until the effect ends. The effect ends early if the creature takes damage or is ever more than 30 feet from you.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Nocturnal Nightmare.</em></strong> As an action during the night, you strike a dissonant chord that scrapes at the hearing organs and cochlear nerves of all creatures in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 16 Constitution saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes [[/r 8d6]] psychic damage and is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.pAcHCDJBhybiVzMF]{Frightened} of you until the end of your next turn. On a success it takes half as much damage and is not frightened of you. After you use this feature, roll a [[/r d4]]. On a 1, all the small feeding medusozoa retreat back into the coral and you can&rsquo;t use this feature again until the next sunset.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"PGyNodV3h1XLslvv","name":"Drider Mask","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Drider_Mask.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This incredibly lightweight picosilk mask is so tactile and responsive that the wearer&rsquo;s expression is fully visible through the mask. The eight eyes have different functions; some provide increased peripheral vision, some are enchanted with divination magic to see a few picoseconds into the future, and some look into &lsquo;the dangerspectrum&rsquo;, a visual representation of incoming doom.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Drider Sense.&nbsp;</strong></em>You have an uncanny ability to sense when something is afoot, an insatiable itch that alerts you to impending danger. While wearing the octonocular mask, you can&rsquo;t be surprised, and creatures don&rsquo;t gain advantage on attack rolls against you as a result of being hidden from you.</p>\n<p>In addition, as a reaction to being the target of an attack or having to make a Dexterity saving throw to avoid damage, you can use your reaction to add your proficiency bonus to your AC or the result of the saving throw, respectively. You do not have to see the source of the attack or effect to do so. Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a short rest.</p>\n<p>If you are @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.tUYvSkhggFcMpVw5]{Incapacitated} by something other than nonmagical sleep, then the Drider Sense feature does not function.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"you are a target of an attack or have to make a Dexterity saving throw to avoid damage"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"sr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["@",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"QX6jIQqaq7pzpLnp","name":"Tome of Living Memories (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tome_of_Living_Memories1.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Wondrous item, uncommon (optional attunement by a wizard)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>The pages of this book are littered with the shifting memories of all the aboleth broodmother's eyes have seen. This deluge of information includes historical occurrences, the gods, and all things arcane, in addition to several spells. Unfortunately, the script is a shifting mire of letters that only the most astute can decipher.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Knowledge from Beyond.</em></strong> Over the course of a minute, you can attempt to discern information from the broodmother's memories. Make a DC 10 Intelligence check. On a success, you gain proficiency in Arcana, History, Nature, and Religion for the next 10 minutes. On a failure, you take psychic damage equal to your level.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Shrouded Spells.</em></strong> In a similar manner, you can spend 10 minutes attempting to cast one of the following spells, requiring no material components and without expending a spell slot. At the end of the 10 minutes, make an Intelligence check. The DC equals 8 plus the spell's level. On a success, you cast the spell. On a failure, you don't cast the spell and you take psychic damage equal to twice the spell's level.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.3OZnNhunvRtPOQmH]{Identify} (1st-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.4v2H3hHb3Ph9XLNd]{Augury} (2nd-level)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.cg50KpBkBdPK6vPL]{Clairvoyance} (3rd-level)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Optional Attunement.</em></strong> <em><strong>Wizard.</strong></em> If you have at least 1 wizard level then you can choose to attune to thismitem. While you remain attuned to it, you can use it as a spellbook and an arcane focus. While you use this tome as your spellbook, the comprehend languages and detect thoughts spells are added to your known spells and you always have them prepared.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":null,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"QZpIeJHfm0gcmMMr","name":"Heart of Stone (Very Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Heart_of_Stone.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Spellcasting focus, very rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>When a fiend dies whilst in close proximity to this fist-sized lump of obsidian, its soul is incarcerated within its inky confines. A creature that attunes to this petrified archdevil's heart learns the name of any soul imprisoned within it and can drain their life force to create powerful magic. However, with each interaction, there is always a chance that the fiend can break free of this crystalline jail.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Soultrap.</em></strong> When a fiend of CR 18 or lower dies within 10 feet of the heart and the heart doesn't already have a soul trapped within it, the fiend's soul becomes trapped within the heart. The heart gains a number of charges equal to the number of hit dice the fiend possesses. If all these charges are used, the soul is shredded and the fiend is destroyed.</p>\n<p>Whenever you hold the stone, you can communicate with the imprisoned soul, if it is willing. You can release an imprisoned soul back to the lower planes as an action.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Soulshred.</em></strong> While you hold the heart, you can expend charges from it to cast the following spells, requiring no material components. If a saving throw is required, the DC is 16.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.95K2aUhAGV9qXjnf]{Bane} (1 charge)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.3MYDjS6k9IYL0aTj]{Calm Emotions} (2 charges)</li>\n<li>enrage (2 charges)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.pO4zGe5LmFIYqJiL]{Bestow Curse} (3 charges)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.XZhdgVK3cLoxNCQl]{Remove Curse} (3 charges)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.ReMbjfeOKoSj3O79]{Stoneskin} (4 charges); when cast, the target's skin resembles the obsidian of the heart</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After you cast a spell using Soulshred, you must make a Charisma check contested by the imprisoned fiend's Charisma check. On a failure, the fiend's soul escapes and is released back to the lower planes and the heart loses all its remaining charges. If a soul escapes while its wielder is on the lower planes, the fiend can immediately materialise.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"heart%20of%20stone%20(very%20rare)_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Heart of Stone (Very Rare)","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"type":"SCF","fluff":{"images":[{"type":"image","href":{"type":"external","url":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Heart_of_Stone.webp"}}]},"rarity":"very rare","reqAttune":true,"entries":["When a fiend dies whilst in close proximity to this fist-sized lump of obsidian, its soul is incarcerated within its inky confines. A creature that attunes to this {@condition petrified} archdevil's heart learns the name of any soul imprisoned within it and can drain their life force to create powerful magic. However, with each interaction, there is always a chance that the fiend can break free of this crystalline jail.",{"type":"entries","name":"Soultrap","entries":["When a fiend of CR 18 or lower dies within 10 feet of the heart and the heart doesn't already have a soul trapped within it, the fiend's soul becomes trapped within the heart. The heart gains a number of charges equal to the number of hit dice the fiend possesses. If all these charges are used, the soul is shredded and the fiend is destroyed.","Whenever you hold the stone, you can communicate with the imprisoned soul, if it is willing. You can release an imprisoned soul back to the lower planes as an action."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Soulshred","entries":["While you hold the heart, you can expend charges from it to cast the following spells, requiring no material components. If a saving throw is required, the DC is 16.","* bane (1 charge)","* calm emotions (2 charges)","* enrage (2 charges)","* bestow curse (3 charges)","* remove curse (3 charges)","stoneskin (4 charges); when cast, the target's skin resembles the obsidian of the heart","After you cast a spell using Soulshred, you must make a Charisma check contested by the imprisoned fiend's Charisma check. On a failure, the fiend's soul escapes and is released back to the lower planes and the heart loses all its remaining charges. If a soul escapes while its wielder is on the lower planes, the fiend can immediately materialise."]}],"uniqueId":"9f7bef89d463876a6951a8cb41be6959","_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["spellcasting focus"],"_typeHtml":"spellcasting focus","_attunement":"(requires attunement)","_attunementCategory":"Requires Attunement","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["Magic"],"_fFocus":[],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBaseItem":[],"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Spellcasting focus"}}}}}
{"_id":"QeoDtfYKFFhs8NVH","name":"Lilipad Sunhat","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Lilipad_Sunhat.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Wondrous item, common (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The water in the top of this hat never sloshes and can&rsquo;t be poured out. It can, however, be scooped out in a drinking vessel. Once water is removed, the hat fills back up over the course of one minute.</p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-57a2fe45-7fff-6ec9-f718-73f748fd92e5\"></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">While you wear the hat outdoors it can photosynthesise and feed you. The time it takes to gain a day&rsquo;s worth of nourishment depends on the brightness: 1 hour in bright, direct sunlight or 8 hours in overcast conditions.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"common","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Gentleman’s Umbershield (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Gentlemans_Umbershield.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wand, spellcasting focus, very rare (requires attunement)</em><br />1 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Rain, arrows, or maces, this wand can deflect it all. Disguised as an oiled blue silk umbrella, as any gentleman might carry, this magical implement gives you a heightened sense of danger. While attuned to the wand, you have advantage on initiative rolls.</p>\n<p>This weapon has 30 charges, and regains [[/r 3d6 + 12]] charges daily at midnight. When you are hit by an attacker you can see, you can use your reaction to open the umbrella. Roll a [[/r d12]]. You expend as many charges as rolled on the [[/r d12]], or as many as remain in the wand, whichever is lower. Until the start of your next turn, your AC increases by the number charges expended. If this stops the attack hitting you, the weapon or missile bounces back at its origin using the original attack roll, potentially causing the attacker to hit itself.</p>\n<p><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong>. An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus, using it in place of any material component which does not list a cost.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":30,"max":"30","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"value":"","foc":true,"amm":false,"hvy":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.magic-items-vol10-victorian-horror.magic-items-vol10-victorian-horror.jzvY3spEziZJSduD"}},"_id":"RqNQ4xXJdd2uL6oH"}
{"_id":"S5711tbcJWols1eT","name":"Magehunter Bulwark (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Bulwark.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Armor (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.sSs3hSzkKBMNBgTs]{Shield}), very rare (requires attunement)</em><br />6 lb.<br />AC +2</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Like a leaden wall, spellbreakers would encircle evil magic users, sending spells ricocheting up into the night sky. Eventually, when the enemy's magic was spent, these red and black shields would thrust forwards, hammering their foe to the ground where they could be shackled. Though few are now found, these mage hunter bulwarks are a thorn in the side of even the mightiest Lich.</p>\n<p>While wielding and attuned to this magical shield, you gain a +1 bonus to your AC and gain the ‘Deflect Spell’ feature.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Deflect Spell.</em></strong> When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken, you can use your reaction to deflect some of the spell’s energy. When you do so, the damage you take from the attack/effect is reduced by [[/r 3d10]].</p>\n<p>If you reduce the damage to 0, the spell has no effect on you, and you can attempt to reflect the spell’s raw energy at its origin. Use the same spell slot level, spell save DC, attack bonus, and/or spellcasting ability of the caster/origin of the spell. On a hit or failed Dexterity saving throw, the target takes force damage equal to the damage absorbed.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, roll a [[/r d6]]. On a 1, the shield becomes overloaded and can’t deflect spells again until you finish a long rest.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d10",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":3,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Sk2IEzywpOBpKJYr","name":"Tidecutter (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tide_Cutter.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword}), melee weapon, rare (requires attunement)</em> <br />3 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] slashing - versatile ([[/r 1d10]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p>This item appears to be a sword hilt stylized with tentacles. While grasping the hilt, you can use a bonus action to cause a blade of rushing water to spring forth, or make it disappear. While the blade exists, this magic longsword has the finesse property. If you are proficient with shortswords or longswords, you are proficient with the <em>tidecutter</em>. You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Water Lash.</em></strong> As an action, you can slash the sword towards a target within 20 feet of you, causing the blade to elongate into a lash. Make a melee weapon attack against the target using this weapon&rsquo;s normal statistics. On a hit you can pull a Large or smaller creature, or an object that weighs 1000 pounds or less, up to 15 feet closer to you. If the target is a fixed object or a Huge or larger creature, you can pull yourself 15 feet towards the target.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Waterborne.</em></strong> When submerged in water, this longsword gains the reach property and the range of the Water Lash feature increases to 30 feet.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Hydrodynamic.</em></strong> Attacking while underwater doesn't impose disadvantage on attack rolls you make with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Versatile.</em></strong> This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the property&mdash;the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+2+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10+2+@mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ver":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Tu8oWbQiOd4LGgtr","name":"Wings of Prey (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Wings_of_Prey_Rainbow.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunemen</em><em>t)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Bestowed upon defenders of city walls and mountain rangers alike, these wings bestow great mobility, as well as packing a secret weapon. The appearance of the wings varies from individual to another, shifting in colour to mirror their soul.</p>\n<p>This item has 6 charges and recharges fully at dawn. While attuned to the wings, you have a flying speed equal to 10 multiplied by the number of remaining charges in feet. As a bonus action, you can speak the command word to make the wings appear or disappear.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Razor Sharp.</em></strong> As an action while the wings are present, you can expend 1 charge to hurl a flurry of razor-sharp feathers in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 8d6]] slashing damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":6,"max":"6","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"UKaAkdYQvpO036vE","name":"Morning Star (Legendary)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Morning_Star.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.dX8AxCh9o0A9CkT3]{Morningstar}), legendary (requires attunement)  </em><br /><em>4 lb.</em><br /><em>[[/r 1d8]] piercing</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Within these four, free-floating, ever-moving, gyroscopic rings is contained the source of <em>morning star</em>'s power: a ball of fusion; a miniaturised star. A creature attuned to the item can induce tiny solar flares that can blind or burn those in its path.</p>\n<p>You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. While attuned you can cast the the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Bnn9Nzajixvow9xi]{Light} cantrip and the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.BP3GCwa66IAw1yTG]{Daylight} spell at will.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Dawn.</em></strong> As an action you can cause <em>morning star</em> to shine a gloriously bright light at all creatures within a 40-foot cone. Each creature in the area must succeed on a DC 17 Constitution saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.995mfaI3z7WtY7vK]{Blinded} until the end of your next turn. One you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Ultraviolet.</em></strong> After you use the Dawn property, but before the next dawn, you can use an action to cause <em>morning star</em> to shine a focussed beam of ultraviolet light in a 5-foot-wide, 300-foot-long line. Each creature in the area must make a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 20d6]] radiant damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until you activate Dawn again.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Eclipse, Set of the Moon and Stars</h2>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\">When the magics of morning star and <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> become intertwined through attunement to a single wielder, their innate dunmantic magics coalesce creating a miniature solar system.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\">While you are attuned to both morning star and <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>, both items gain an additional +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, the saving throw DCs of both items are increased by 1 , and you can use the Orbit and Eclipse properties.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Orbit.</span></strong> Whenever you make a ranged attack with <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> while also holding morning star, you can use a bonus action to cause it to begin orbiting you. As part of this bonus action and as a bonus action on subsequent turns, you can make one attack with <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> against any creature within 15 feet of you.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Evening moon</span> orbits you at a distance of [[/r 1d3]] feet. Any creature within 5 feet of you can use its action to make a DC 21 Dexterity (Acrobatics) check in an attempt to catch <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>. On a success, the creature catches <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>. On a failure, it takes [[/r 1d6]] slashing damage.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eclipse.</span></strong> As a bonus action while <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> is orbiting you, you can cause it to hover in front of you, casting you in a dark obscuring light. For the next minute you are under the effects of the blur spell. You must concentrate on Eclipse as if you were concentrating on a spell. After you activate this effect, you can’t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+2+@mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VG3aH04uYdsuAZ83","name":"Sleuth's Shadowcoat (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sleuths_Shadowcoat.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Sometimes a detective’s best tool is remaining unde - tected. The sleuth’s shadowcoat allows its wearer to take full advantage of shadows, to hide in plain sight, and to disappear in a puff of smoke (well… fog) when things go awry. Also, it has plenty of secret and obvi - ous pockets in which to store things. Very useful.</p>\n<p>This item has 15 charges and regains [[/r 1d10 + 5]] expended charges daily at dawn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Shadow Stealth.</strong></em> While in anything but bright, direct sunlight, you can expend 1 charge as a bonus action to turn invis - ible until the start of your next turn. If you use your bonus action to spend 1 charge at the start of your next turn, this effect continues without interruption.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Hide in Plain Sight. </strong></em>As an action, you can spend 2 charges to cast the @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.JShwwDrTzHTvgN7Y]{Chameleon Skin} spell on yourself.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Disappearing Act.</strong></em> As an action, you can expend 2 charges to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} spell centred on yourself, and immediately move up to half your speed. @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} has a duration of Concentration, up to 1 minute, when cast in this way. You can expend additional 3 charges (to a total of 5) to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.2IWiZAJtOGDoKjiz]{Gaseous Form} spell on yourself immediately before you move.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":15,"max":"15","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.yn4L2huBrmpRlI3m"}}}
{"_id":"VXsMAhEoxz9WlBs9","name":"Tidecutter (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tide_Cutter.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword}), melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement)</em> <br />3 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] slashing - versatile ([[/r 1d10]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p>This item appears to be a sword hilt stylized with tentacles. While grasping the hilt, you can use a bonus action to cause a blade of rushing water to spring forth, or make it disappear. While the blade exists, this magic longsword has the finesse property. If you are proficient with shortswords or longswords, you are proficient with the <em>tidecutter</em>. You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Water Lash.</em></strong> As an action, you can slash the sword towards a target within 20 feet of you, causing the blade to elongate into a lash. Make a melee weapon attack against the target using this weapon&rsquo;s normal statistics. On a hit you can pull a Medium or smaller creature, or an object that weighs 500 pounds or less, up to 15 feet closer to you. If the target is a fixed object or a Huge or larger creature, you can pull yourself 15 feet towards the target.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Waterborne.</em></strong> When submerged in water, this longsword gains the reach property and the range of the Water Lash feature increases to 30 feet.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Hydrodynamic.</em></strong> Attacking while underwater doesn't impose disadvantage on attack rolls you make with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Versatile.</em></strong> This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the property&mdash;the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+1+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10+1+@mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ver":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XBdsT1nCGlYUsOKJ","name":"Clockwork Wyvern","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Clockwork_Wyvern.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This limited edition @Compendium[magic-items-vol0-free-for-all.bestiary-vol0-free-for-all.hyiI4RVmEbKu1btd]{Clockwork Wyvern} comes with a fully-operational, miniature coal engine. Thanks to an intricate mix of steam-powered gears and pistons, the construct has lifelike movements and mannerisms.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Combat.</em></strong> In combat, the <em>Clockwork Wyvern</em> shares your initiative count, but takes its turn immediately after yours. It can move and use its reaction on it’s own, but the only action it takes on its turn is the Dodge action, unless you take a bonus action on your turn to command it to take the action in its stat block or the Dash, Disengage, Help, Hide or Search action.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Death and Damage.</em></strong> The <em>clockwork wyvern</em> cannot regain hit points like other creatures. If the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.kjmjY0zlE6IEiQVL]{Mending}spell is cast on it, it regains [[/r 2d6]] hit points. If it falls to 0 hit points, it loses all charges and becomes inert. Lightning or fire damage from a first level spell or higher can reinvigorate the wyvern, bringing it back to life with 0 charges.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.magic-items-vol6-magitech-mayhem.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.XBdsT1nCGlYUsOKJ"}}}
{"_id":"XX2v3qBfUo8vi9oQ","name":"Cone of Frosting","type":"spell","img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/blue_30.jpg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\">Swirling your hands in a clockwise fashion, a torrent of sticky, freezing sugar shoots forth from your outstretched fingertips. Each creature in a 15-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes [[/r 3d4]] cold damage and its speed is reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn. On a success, a creature takes half as much damage and is not slowed.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d4]] for each slot level above 1st.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Humperdink's Wares","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d4","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ZSmR50wrEMgDzCfA","name":"Eyes of the Forgotten (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Eyes_of_the_Forgotten.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Ring, rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>The barnacle-like yellow eyes that adorn this ring flick to and fro with reptilian suddenness. When you make eye contact with one of them, brief feelings of drowsiness, terror, and nausea wash over you before it darts away once more.</p>\n<p>This ring has <strong>3 charges</strong>, represented by the 3 open eyes. The ring regains <strong>[[/r 1d2 + 1]]</strong> charges daily at midnight. As an action you can expend a charge, thrusting the ring towards a creature you can see within <strong>60 feet</strong> while speaking the command word and causing one of the ring’s eyes to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.ZRqu3Xh9FmlBCZGy]{Eyebite} spell (<strong>save DC 15</strong>) with a duration of <strong>1 minute</strong> (no concentration required).</p>\n<p>For the duration a creature is affected, the eye on the ring becomes an inky void, imbued with dread power. If a save is succeeded, or when the duration elapses, the eye closes.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ZcqjNkEbohoTU80l","name":"Mechanical Tail (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Mechanical_Tail.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This item is another creation of the eccentric Anton Spark, tinkerer extraordinaire. This mechanical tail is powered by a magic-infused steam core. Any bipedal creature can wear it on its back and, once attuned, use it as if it was born with a tail.</p>\n<p>While attuned to the mechanical tail you can use it to grapple a target within reach. You have +3 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks you make to grapple a target with this tail.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Steam-powered Strike.</em></strong> As an action, you sweep your tail with wicked, steam-powered ferocity. Each creature within 5 feet of your must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 3d8]] slashing damage and be knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. Roll a [[/r d4]]; on a 1 the tail runs out of steam and can't be used again until you finish a short rest</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ZvaNIMTzoypYhb5m","name":"Mechanical Tail (Legendary)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Mechanical_Tail.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This item is another creation of the eccentric Anton Spark, tinkerer extraordinaire. This mechanical tail is powered by a magic-infused steam core. Any bipedal creature can wear it on its back and, once attuned, use it as if it was born with a tail.</p>\n<p>While attuned to the mechanical tail you can use it to grapple a target within reach. You have +6 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks you make to grapple a target with this tail.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Steam-powered Strike.</em></strong> As an action, you sweep your tail with wicked, steam-powered ferocity. Each creature within 5 feet of your must succeed on a DC 19 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 5d10]] slashing damage and be knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. Roll a [[/r d4]]; on a 1 the tail runs out of steam and can't be used again until you finish a short rest</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":19,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"aadWKVmxX5e0TGKa","name":"Chakram","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/shuriken-triple-purple.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon</em></p>\n<p><em> [[/r 1d6]] slashing - finesse, light, thrown (30/90 ft.)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Thrown.</em></strong> If a weapon has the thrown property, you can throw the weapon to make a ranged attack. If the weapon is a melee weapon, you use the same ability modifier for that attack roll and damage roll that you would use for a melee attack with the weapon. For example, if you throw a handaxe, you use your Strength, but if you throw a dagger, you can use either your Strength or your Dexterity, since the dagger has the finesse property.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"","identified":false,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":90,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"thr":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"afhh0nIxTTotkeEi","name":"Purple Wyrmfist (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Purple_Wyrmfist.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tWondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t  \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<hr />\n\t\t<p>From the striking violet chitin of the subterranean purple worm is crafted this surprisingly tactile gauntlet. Each day, the gauntlet produces a diluted version of the worm's toxin that is able to cause debilitating pain through a single touch. Purple worm chitin is a sound enhancer, able to amplify vibrations and grant its wearer the ability to detect the slightest tremor.</p><p><strong><em>Purple Poison.</em></strong> As a bonus action you can cause the gauntlet to secrete a purple worm toxin. The next time you hit a creature with an unarmed strike, or successfully grapple a creature, the creature must make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 4d6]] poison damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. After you activate this property, roll a [[/r d4]]. On a 1 or 2 you can't activate this property again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":"you successfully hit or grapple a creature with an unarmed strike"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d6","poison"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bs8hlL6wDs8mS0Zz","name":"Magehunter Blade (Legendary)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Blade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Generic variant, legendary (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Made of a weave-intersecting alloy, these armaments were the go-to weapon for the mage-hunting Order of the Spellbreakers. Fanatical elements within the order have recently taken power, bringing with them an abhorrence for all things magical. Having largely destroyed this magical cache, such weapons are now very rare and are only wielded by the few who cling to the old ways.</p>\n<p>You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. If you hit a target that is under the effect of a spell or magical effect, the spell is dispelled if it is 7th-level or lower, and the target takes an additional [[/r 1d8]] force damage for each level of the dispelled spell (dispelled cantrips deal no additional damage). Once a spell is dispelled, roll a [[/r d8]]. If the number is equal to or lower than the level of the dispelled spell, the blade loses this feature until the following dawn.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.xMkP8BmFzElcsMaR]{Greatsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.Dh8iumgXhySO81Xl]{Magehunter Greatsword (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.PsfxRMmhRBYawd8Q]{Magehunter Longsword (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.2RcILBdCGYsinuuW]{Magehunter Rapier (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.n2Na3Nps4xwMAZRg]{Magehunter Scimitar (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.osLzOwQdPtrK3rQH]{Shortsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.uM78F1sRT1Ebw84X]{Magehunter Shortsword (Legendary)})</li>\n</ul>\n\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ffNCh8f8ZfwJQIJE","name":"Magehunter Bulwark (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Bulwark.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Armor (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.sSs3hSzkKBMNBgTs]{Shield}), uncommon (requires attunement)</em><br />6 lb.<br />AC +2</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Like a leaden wall, spellbreakers would encircle evil magic users, sending spells ricocheting up into the night sky. Eventually, when the enemy's magic was spent, these red and black shields would thrust forwards, hammering their foe to the ground where they could be shackled. Though few are now found, these mage hunter bulwarks are a thorn in the side of even the mightiest Lich.</p>\n<p>While wielding and attuned to this magical shield, you gain the ‘Deflect Spell’ feature.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Deflect Spell.</em></strong> When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken, you can use your reaction to deflect some of the spell’s energy. When you do so, the damage you take from the attack/effect is reduced by [[/r 1d10]].</p>\n<p>If you reduce the damage to 0, the spell has no effect on you, and you can attempt to reflect the spell’s raw energy at its origin. Use the same spell slot level, spell save DC, attack bonus, and/or spellcasting ability of the caster/origin of the spell. On a hit or failed Dexterity saving throw, the target takes force damage equal to the damage absorbed.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, roll a [[/r d6]]. On a 1, the shield becomes overloaded and can’t deflect spells again until you finish a long rest.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"gq5MBYIBbVYatHoZ","name":"Arclight Rapier (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Arclight_Rapier.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier}), rare <br />Martial weapon, melee weapon <br />2 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] piercing - finesse</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A tool-weapon inspired by the Clockwork Nirvana, a plane of precise law and order, this blade is equally capable of repairing mechanical marvels or incapacitating malfunctioning automatons. On the Material Plane, such weapons are carried by tech-priests, holy clerics whose altar is a workbench and whose sermon is the clang of a hammer on an anvil.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon has 10 charges and regains [[/r 1d8 + 2]] charges daily at dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Arclight Weld.</em></strong> When you hit a target with a weapon attack using this weapon you can pull a concealed trigger to expend a charge and cause a flash of lightning to burst from your weapon. The target takes an additional [[/r 1d8]] lightning damage. In addition, if the target is made of non-magical metal or is a creature wearing non-magical metal armour, it must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or have the metal become welded. While wearing welded armour, or while its body is welded, the creature gains the welded condition: its speed is reduced by 10 feet for each welded stack it has accumulated.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Unwelding.</em></strong> All stacks of the welded condition can be ended in one of two ways: brute force or delicate tinkering.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Brute Force. A welded creature can use its action to make a DC 15 Strength check. On a success, it removes the welded condition but damages the metal, gaining a permanent -1 to its AC while it wears the armour, until the armour is repaired. On a failure, nothing happens.</li>\n<li>Tinkering. A creature can spend 10 minutes to make a DC 15 Dexterity (smith's or tinkerer's tools)* check. On a success, it ends the welded condition. On a failure, it ends the welded condition but damages the metal, conferring a permanent -1 to its AC while it wears the armour, until the armour is repaired.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":10,"max":"10","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","piercing"],["1d8","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"arclight%20rapier%20(rare)_lootavern","propDroppable":"item"}}}
{"_id":"gss2GdJgVqSNvVAr","name":"Gullinbursti Tusks (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Gullinbursti_Tusks.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Simple weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger}), melee weapon, very rare (requires attunement)</em><br />1 lb.<br />[[/r 1d4]] piercing - finesse, light, thrown (20/60 ft.)</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These rough, gold-and-ivory daggers are said to have been forged using leftover materials from the forging of Gullinbursti, the great Golden boar. A restless aura suffuses these blades, from its golden-haired hilt to its ivory points. Attuning to both daggers requires a single attunement slot. While wielding both daggers you can use the <em>Boar&rsquo;s Charge</em> and <em>Spirit of the Golden Boar</em> properties.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with these weapons.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><em>Boar&rsquo;s Charge. </em></strong>If you move at least 20 feet straight towards a creature and then hit it with an attack using the tusk the same turn, the target takes an additional [[/r 4d6]] piercing damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a DC 16 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Spirit of the Golden Boar. </em></strong>You call forth Gullinbursti&rsquo;s residual power. As an action, you speak the command word and point your daggers at a point you can see within 30 feet of you. A spectral golden boar charges in a straight line from you to the point. All creatures along this line must make a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 10d6]] radiant damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. Once you use this property, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":2,"weight":1,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"enemy"},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod + 2","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"mgc":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hNpT66v83QNMmbpB","name":"Evening Moon (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Evening_Moon.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon, rare (requires attunement)&nbsp; </em></p>\n<p><em>[[/r 1d6]] slashing - finesse, light, thrown (30/90 ft.)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This three-quarter chakram can sustain itself in flight, returning to its wielder after lacerating its target. Equally lethal in both melee and ranged combat, this weapon is favoured by assassins of the astral sea for its ability to create a moving sphere of shadow, aiding its wielder to slip through enemy lines unseen, even in broad daylight.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon grants a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it, and it returns to your hand immediately after it is used to make a ranged attack. When you hit a creature with the shapechanger tag with this weapon, the creature must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or instantly revert to its original form and be unable to assume a different form for the next minute.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Dusk.</em></strong> While you hold this item you can, as an action, create a 20-foot sphere centred on you in which all light becomes dim. This sphere lasts for 1 hour, or until you dismiss it as a bonus action, and it follows you when you move. While Dusk is active, you can hide when only lightly obscured, and you can take the Hide action as a bonus action. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dusk.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2>Eclipse, Set of the Moon and Stars</h2>\n<p>When the magics of morning star and <em>evening moon</em> become intertwined through attunement to a single wielder, their innate dunmantic magics coalesce creating a miniature solar system.</p>\n<p>While you are attuned to both morning star and <em>evening moon</em>, both items gain an additional +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, the saving throw DCs of both items are increased by 1 , and you can use the Orbit and Eclipse properties.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Orbit.</em></strong> Whenever you make a ranged attack with <em>evening moon</em> while also holding morning star, you can use a bonus action to cause it to begin orbiting you. As part of this bonus action and as a bonus action on subsequent turns, you can make one attack with <em>evening moon</em> against any creature within 15 feet of you.</p>\n<p><em>Evening moon</em> orbits you at a distance of [[/r 1d3]] feet. Any creature within 5 feet of you can use its action to make a DC 21 Dexterity (Acrobatics) check in an attempt to catch <em>evening moon</em>. On a success, the creature catches <em>evening moon</em>. On a failure, it takes [[/r 1d6]] slashing damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Eclipse.</em></strong> As a bonus action while <em>evening moon</em> is orbiting you, you can cause it to hover in front of you, casting you in a dark obscuring light. For the next minute you are under the effects of the blur spell. You must concentrate on Eclipse as if you were concentrating on a spell. After you activate this effect, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Thrown.</em></strong> If a weapon has the thrown property, you can throw the weapon to make a ranged attack. If the weapon is a melee weapon, you use the same ability modifier for that attack roll and damage roll that you would use for a melee attack with the weapon. For example, if you throw a handaxe, you use your Strength, but if you throw a dagger, you can use either your Strength or your Dexterity, since the dagger has the finesse property.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":90,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+1+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"thr":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hdOwQcAjdeV1KpIP","name":"Arclight Rapier (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Arclight_Rapier.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier}), very rare <br />Martial weapon, melee weapon <br />2 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] piercing - finesse</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A tool-weapon inspired by the Clockwork Nirvana, a plane of precise law and order, this blade is equally capable of repairing mechanical marvels or incapacitating malfunctioning automatons. On the Material Plane, such weapons are carried by tech-priests, holy clerics whose altar is a workbench and whose sermon is the clang of a hammer on an anvil.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon has 12 charges and regains [[/r 1d10 + 2]] charges daily at dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Arclight Weld.</em></strong> When you hit a target with a weapon attack using this weapon you can pull a concealed trigger to expend a charge and cause a flash of lightning to burst from your weapon. The target takes an additional [[/r 2d6]] lightning damage. In addition, if the target is made of non-magical metal or is a creature wearing non-magical metal armour, it must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or have the metal become welded. While wearing welded armour, or while its body is welded, the creature gains the welded condition: its speed is reduced by 10 feet for each welded stack it has accumulated.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Unwelding.</em></strong> All stacks of the welded condition can be ended in one of two ways: brute force or delicate tinkering.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Brute Force. A welded creature can use its action to make a DC 15 Strength check. On a success, it removes the welded condition but damages the metal, gaining a permanent -1 to its AC while it wears the armour, until the armour is repaired. On a failure, nothing happens.</li>\n<li>Tinkering. A creature can spend 10 minutes to make a DC 15 Dexterity (smith's or tinkerer's tools)* check. On a success, it ends the welded condition. On a failure, it ends the welded condition but damages the metal, conferring a permanent -1 to its AC while it wears the armour, until the armour is repaired.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":12,"max":"12","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","piercing"],["2d6","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hiEX0812mVXTrjb7","name":"Concubine's War Fan (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Concubines_War_Fan.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Some assassins rely on stealth. Others, like the concubines of the Courteous Cabal, prefer to hide in plain sight, beguiling their quarry into a stupor before finishing them off with a quick slash.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Weapon.</em></strong>&nbsp;This magic fan can be used as a martial melee weapon. It has the finesse, light, and thrown (20/60 ft.) properties; and deals slashing damage equal to [[/r 1d6]] plus your ability modifier on a hit. Ranged weapon attacks made with this fan ignore half cover.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Beguiling Dance.</em></strong>&nbsp;As an action while holding the fan you can begin a slow, hypnotic dance, causing the fan to glow with an ephemeral, beguiling light. Each humanoid of your choice within 15 feet of you must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw contested by your Charisma (Performance) check or be charmed by you until you stop dancing. If you use your bonus action at the start of each turn to continue dancing, any charmed creatures remained charmed. The charm ends early if you're ever more than 15 feet from your target or if you or your companions do anything harmful to it. When the effect ends, the creature knows it was charmed by you. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Optional Attunement.</em></strong>&nbsp;While attuned to this fan you are proficient with it and you have advantage on Charisma (Performance) checks you make while holding this fan.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"mgc":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"idnz2IOtBAyv7x20","name":"Coralborn Harp (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Coralborn_Harp.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, instrument, rare (requires attunement)</em> <br /><br />2 lb.<br /></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Coralborn have two genres of music; diurnal and nocturnal. The diurnal celebrates the reef&rsquo;s colour, community, and biodiversity; it is often uplifting and joyful. The nocturnal illustrates the hunt, when sharks prowl, and the millions of tiny medusozoa that make up the coral feed. Though this harp can play any type of music, the time of day can accentuate its magical capabilities.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Diurnal Dream.</em></strong> As an action during the day, you can play one of the following tunes, targeting one creature that can hear you within 30 feet, which must make a DC 14 Wisdom saving throw. If the effect ends at the start of your next turn and you immediately use your action at the start of your turn to continue playing the same tune, the effect continues, no saving throw required.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Charming Melody.</em></strong> On a failed save, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.H8aTFVG3YFAkQ3TK]{Charmed}&nbsp;until the start of your next turn. The effect ends early if you or any of your allies harm the creature. When the effect ends, the creature knows it was charmed by you.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Gentle Lullaby.</em></strong> The creature falls @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.MOk1rkF0DeJlcC4l]{Unconscious} until the end of your next turn. A creature that has legs falls @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}&nbsp;when it falls asleep (at the GM&rsquo;s discretion). The effect ends early if the creature takes damage or if someone uses an action to shake the creature awake.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Mesmerising Canon.</em></strong> The creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.tUYvSkhggFcMpVw5]{Incapacitated}&nbsp;until the start of your next turn, using all its movement to follow you. If it is unable to follow the harpist, or if doing so would result in the creature being harmed, it remains motionless until the effect ends. The effect ends early if the creature takes damage or is ever more than 30 feet from you.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Nocturnal Nightmare.</em></strong> As an action during the night, you strike a dissonant chord that scrapes at the hearing organs and cochlear nerves of all creatures in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes [[/r 4d6]] psychic damage and is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.pAcHCDJBhybiVzMF]{Frightened} of you until the end of your next turn. On a success it takes half as much damage and is not frightened of you. After you use this feature, roll a [[/r d4]]. On a 1, all the small feeding medusozoa retreat back into the coral and you can&rsquo;t use this feature again until the next sunset.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jebHIO1rXtN8ZGLj","name":"Sleuth's Shadowcoat (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sleuths_Shadowcoat.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Sometimes a detective’s best tool is remaining unde - tected. The sleuth’s shadowcoat allows its wearer to take full advantage of shadows, to hide in plain sight, and to disappear in a puff of smoke (well… fog) when things go awry. Also, it has plenty of secret and obvi - ous pockets in which to store things. Very useful.</p>\n<p>This item has 15 charges and regains [[/r 1d10 + 5]] expended charges daily at dawn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Shadow Stealth.</strong></em> While in anything but bright, direct sunlight, you can expend 1 charge as a bonus action to turn invis - ible until the start of your next turn. If you use your bonus action to spend 1 charge at the start of your next turn, this effect continues without interruption. This invisibility ends if you attack or cast a spell.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Hide in Plain Sight. </strong></em>As an action, you can spend 2 charges to cast the @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.JShwwDrTzHTvgN7Y]{Chameleon Skin} spell on yourself.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Disappearing Act.</strong></em> As an action, you can expend 2 charges to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} spell centred on yourself, and immediately move up to half your speed. @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} has a duration of Concentration, up to 1 minute, when cast in this way.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":15,"max":"15","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KQGYr9UtTjBy4aGj"}}}
{"_id":"jmTq7UBLie3jfU8t","name":"Phantom Blade Greatsword","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantomblade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Martial weapon, melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement) <br />6 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Branton bodged this project up so badly he actually managed to kill the sword. \"Swords aren't even alive\", I hear you say. You're right, they're not. Branton Quark's control of magic is so porous that he not only managed to grant an inanimate object life but, while it was revelling in its new-found consciousness, kill it again almost immediately. The sword is now pissed and haunts any who takes the life of a sentient being. This blade is an almost permanent fixture in the FBI evidence lockers; no-one is quite sure if sword murder is actually an offence.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon deals an extra [[/r 1d4]] psychic damage to any target it hits. This damage is doubled against ethereal targets, such as ghosts and shadows.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Poltergeist.</em></strong> Whenever you kill a non-ethereal creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or more, the phantom blade—or Kaspa as it calls itself—haunts you. You must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or develop one short-term madness effect.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sentience.</em></strong> Kaspa the phantom blade is a sentient, lawful neutral item with an Intelligence of 14, a Wisdom of 12, and a Charisma of 12. It has hearing and</p>\n<p><strong><em>Heavy.</em></strong> Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Two-Handed.</em></strong> This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6+@mod","slashing"],["1d4","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"hvy":true,"two":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"phantom%20blade%20greatsword_lootavern","propDroppable":"item"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.a.jNsEjUISWO3ifmiA"}}}
{"_id":"jzvY3spEziZJSduD","name":"Gentleman’s Umbershield (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Gentlemans_Umbershield.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wand, spellcasting focus, rare (requires attunement)</em><br />1 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Rain, arrows, or maces, this wand can deflect it all. Disguised as an oiled blue silk umbrella, as any gentleman might carry, this magical implement gives you a heightened sense of danger. While attuned to the wand, you have advantage on initiative rolls.</p>\n<p>This weapon has 20 charges, and regains [[/r 1d10 + 10]] charges daily at midnight. When you are hit by an attacker you can see, you can use your reaction to open the umbrella. Roll a [[/r d10]]. You expend as many charges as rolled on the [[/r d10]], or as many as remain in the wand, whichever is lower. Until the start of your next turn, your AC increases by the number charges expended. If this stops the attack hitting you, the weapon or missile bounces back at its origin using the original attack roll, potentially causing the attacker to hit itself.</p>\n<p><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong>. An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus, using it in place of any material component which does not list a cost.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":20,"max":"20","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"value":"","foc":true,"amm":false,"hvy":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"k0ykc3zWMh4yyDrn","name":"Flail of the Elder Deacon (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Flail_of_the_Elder_Deacon.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.UrH3sMdnUDckIHJ6]{Flail}), melee weapon, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This solid steel incense dispenser dangles at the end of a black metal chain. The heady perfume of incense and myrrh follow in the wake of the bearer of this weighty, magical weapon.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon, which has 5 charges. To recharge the flail, you must perform a one-hour ritual between dawn and dusk, consuming quality incense with a value in gold pieces equal to three times the number of charges you wish to regain.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As an action you can cast the following spells (save DC 13), expending at least the number of charges indicated and requiring no material components. For each additional charge expended above the number indicated, the slot level of the cast spell increases by one.</p>\n<p></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IBJmWjzbQGu7M4UX]{Fog Cloud} - 1 charge</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.wqfAVANuQonNBgnL]{Misty Step} - 2 charges</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.TwlD4PLcltv7Xh7j]{Stinking Cloud} - 3 charges</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.LkvI11Uue774QBKZ]{Cloudkill} - 5 charges</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod+2","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wxRE0OgtvHB77jDH"}}}
{"_id":"k22URJvzPRACULZ9","name":"Phantom Blade Longsword","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantomblade.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Martial weapon, melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement) <br />3 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Branton bodged this project up so badly he actually managed to kill the sword. \"Swords aren't even alive\", I hear you say. You're right, they're not. Branton Quark's control of magic is so porous that he not only managed to grant an inanimate object life but, while it was revelling in its new-found consciousness, kill it again almost immediately. The sword is now pissed and haunts any who takes the life of a sentient being. This blade is an almost permanent fixture in the FBI evidence lockers; no-one is quite sure if sword murder is actually an offence.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon deals an extra [[/r 1d4]] psychic damage to any target it hits. This damage is doubled against ethereal targets, such as ghosts and shadows.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Poltergeist.</em></strong> Whenever you kill a non-ethereal creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or more, the phantom blade—or Kaspa as it calls itself—haunts you. You must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or develop one short-term madness effect.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Sentience.</em></strong> Kaspa the phantom blade is a sentient, lawful neutral item with an Intelligence of 14, a Wisdom of 12, and a Charisma of 12. It has hearing and</p>\n<p><strong><em>Versatile.</em></strong> This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the property—the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","slashing"],["1d4","psychic"]],"versatile":"1d10+@mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ver":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"phantom%20blade%20longsword_lootavern","propDroppable":"item"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.a.hTb6zzJrVRS6l4o0"}}}
{"name":"Gentleman’s Umbershield (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Gentlemans_Umbershield.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wand, spellcasting focus, uncommon (requires attunement)</em><br />1 lb.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Rain, arrows, or maces, this wand can deflect it all. Disguised as an oiled blue silk umbrella, as any gentleman might carry, this magical implement gives you a heightened sense of danger. While attuned to the wand, you have advantage on initiative rolls.</p>\n<p>This weapon has 12 charges, and regains [[/r 1d6 + 6]] charges daily at midnight. When you are hit by an attacker you can see, you can use your reaction to open the umbrella. Roll a [[/r d8]]. You expend as many charges as rolled on the [[/r d8]], or as many as remain in the wand, whichever is lower. Until the start of your next turn, your AC increases by the number charges expended. If this stops the attack hitting you, the weapon or missile bounces back at its origin using the original attack roll, potentially causing the attacker to hit itself.</p>\n<p><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong>. An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus, using it in place of any material component which does not list a cost.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":12,"max":"12","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"value":"","foc":true,"amm":false,"hvy":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.magic-items-vol10-victorian-horror.magic-items-vol10-victorian-horror.jzvY3spEziZJSduD"}},"_id":"kdyk8C9tW0NgNyDe"}
{"_id":"krYb2MWhHKd4ZXzw","name":"Evening Moon (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Evening_Moon.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<p><em>[[/r 1d6]] slashing - finesse, light, thrown (30/90 ft.)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This three-quarter chakram can sustain itself in flight, returning to its wielder after lacerating its target. Equally lethal in both melee and ranged combat, this weapon is favoured by assassins of the astral sea for its ability to create a moving sphere of shadow, aiding its wielder to slip through enemy lines unseen, even in broad daylight.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon returns to your hand immediately after it is used to make a ranged attack. When you hit a creature with the shapechanger tag with this weapon, the creature must succeed on a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or instantly revert to its original form and be unable to assume a different form for the next minute.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Dusk.</em></strong> While you hold this item you can, as an action, create a 20-foot sphere centred on you in which all light becomes dim. This sphere lasts for 10 minutes, or until you dismiss it as a bonus action, and it follows you when you move. While Dusk is active, you can hide when only lightly obscured, and you can take the Hide action as a bonus action. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dusk.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Light.</em></strong> A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Thrown.</em></strong> If a weapon has the thrown property, you can throw the weapon to make a ranged attack. If the weapon is a melee weapon, you use the same ability modifier for that attack roll and damage roll that you would use for a melee attack with the weapon. For example, if you throw a handaxe, you use your Strength, but if you throw a dagger, you can use either your Strength or your Dexterity, since the dagger has the finesse property.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":90,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"lgt":true,"thr":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lCpbSDnLCrrtOB0b","name":"Peppermint Plate","type":"spell","img":"icons/commodities/materials/material-feathers-purple.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A protective layer of hot, hard peppermint icing coats you. For the spell&rsquo;s duration, you gain a +1 bonus to your AC and, if a creature hits you with a melee attack, the creature takes [[/r 2d4]] fire damage.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em>&nbsp;When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the fire damage increases by [[/r 1d4]] for each slot level above 1st.</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Class:</strong>&nbsp;Paladin, Sorcerer, Warlock, Wizard</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"well-chewed peppermint chewing gum","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"liayWQ4RPkXB3CYI","name":"Tidecutter (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Tide_Cutter.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword}), melee weapon, very rare (requires attunement)</em> <br />3 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] slashing - versatile ([[/r 1d10]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p>This item appears to be a sword hilt stylized with tentacles. While grasping the hilt, you can use a bonus action to cause a blade of rushing water to spring forth, or make it disappear. While the blade exists, this magic longsword has the finesse property. If you are proficient with shortswords or longswords, you are proficient with the <em>tidecutter</em>. You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Water Lash.</em></strong> As an action, you can slash the sword towards a target within 30 feet of you, causing the blade to elongate into a lash. Make a melee weapon attack against the target using this weapon&rsquo;s normal statistics. On a hit you can pull a Huge or smaller creature, or an object that weighs 2000 pounds or less, up to 25 feet closer to you. If the target is a fixed object or a Huge or larger creature, you can pull yourself 25 feet towards the target.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Waterborne.</em></strong> When submerged in water, this longsword gains the reach property and the range of the Water Lash feature increases to 40 feet.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Hydrodynamic.</em></strong> Attacking while underwater doesn't impose disadvantage on attack rolls you make with this weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Versatile.</em></strong> This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the property&mdash;the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+3","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+3+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10+3+@mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ver":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"mCCHidqNZY99hQ8o","name":"Coralskin","type":"spell","img":"icons/commodities/biological/suckers-green.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a willing creature, turning their skin into a rapidly growing landscape of varicoloured coral. When the spell is cast, and at the start of each of the target creature&rsquo;s turns for the duration of the spell, the creature gains temporary hit points equal to&nbsp;[[/r 2d4]] plus your spellcasting ability modifier. In addition, the target&rsquo;s unarmed attacks deal an additional [[/r 1d4]] slashing damage on a hit. When the spell ends, the target loses any remaining temporary hit points from this spell.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em>&nbsp;When you cast this spell using a slot of 3rd level or higher, the number of temporary hit points gained increases by [[/r 1d4]] for each slot level above 2nd.</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Druid, Ranger, Sorcerer, Wizard</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Humperdink's Wares","activation":{"type":"action","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4+@mod","temphp"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a lump of living coral","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d4"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pUivTN81fvbPks7u"}}}
{"_id":"mKf808ytz6c1TJem","name":"Glaive of the Green Tyrant (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glaive_of_the_Green_Tyrant.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.rOG1OM2ihgPjOvFW]{Glaive}), melee weapon, rare (requires attunement)</em> <br />6 lb.<br />[[/r 1d10]] slashing - heavy, reach, two-handed</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Legend tells of a great warrior queen who, having bested a bronze dragon in a game of wits, sought the ability to wield the power of storms. With this power, she laid waste to entire armies, throwing them back into the ranks of their allies, or burning them with flashes of incandescent lightning. Some called her liberator, others: tyrant. Though defeated by the Hero in Red, some of her power yet remains in the Green Tyrant's ancient glaive.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Summon Storm.</em></strong> With a flourish of the glaive you can expend a bonus action to whip up a tornado - 5-foot-diameter, 30-foot-high cylinder of rushing air and crackling lightning - centred on a point within 60 feet. The tornado lasts for 1 minute. Each creature that starts its turn in the tornado's space or enters the space for the first time on a turn must make a DC 15 Strength saving throw. On a failure, a creature is thrown 10 feet in a random direction, landing prone, and takes [[/r 1d6]] bludgeoning and [[/r 1d6]] lightning damage. Roll a [[/r d8]] to determine the direction: 1, north; 2, northeast; 3, east; 4, southeast; 5, south; 6, southwest; 7, west; or 8 northwest.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action on your turn while the tornado is conjured, you can move the tornado up to 20 feet. Each creature whose space the tornado moves through must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d6]] lightning damage. A creature can't take damage from this effect more than once per turn.</p>\n<p>Once you use the Summon Storm property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Heavy.</em></strong> Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Reach.</em></strong> This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Two-Handed.</em></strong> This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"hvy":true,"rch":true,"two":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"glaive%20of%20the%20green%20tyrant%20(rare)_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Glaive of the Green Tyrant (Rare)","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"fluff":{"images":[{"type":"image","href":{"type":"external","url":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glaive_of_the_Green_Tyrant.webp"}}]},"baseItem":"glaive