 With this power, she laid waste to entire armies, throwing them back into the ranks of their allies, or burning them with flashes of incandescent lightning. Some called her liberator, others: tyrant. Though defeated by the Hero in Red, some of her power yet remains in the Green Tyrant's ancient glaive.",{"type":"entries","name":"Summon Storm","entries":["With a flourish of the glaive you can expend a bonus action to whip up a tornado - 5-foot-diameter, 30-foot-high cylinder of rushing air and crackling lightning - centred on a point within 60 feet. The tornado lasts for 1 minute. Each creature that starts its turn in the tornado's space or enters the space for the first time on a turn must make a DC 15 Strength saving throw. On a failure, a creature is thrown 10 feet in a random direction, landing {@condition prone}, and takes {@dice 1d6} bludgeoning and {@damage 1d6} lightning damage. Roll a {@dice d8} to determine the direction: 1, north; 2, northeast; 3, east; 4, southeast; 5, south; 6, southwest; 7, west; or 8 northwest.","As a bonus action on your turn while the tornado is conjured, you can move the tornado up to 20 feet. Each creature whose space the tornado moves through must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or take {@damage 1d6} lightning damage. A creature can't take damage from this effect more than once per turn.","Once you use the Summon Storm property, you can't do so again until the following dawn."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Heavy","entries":["Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Reach","entries":["This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Two-Handed","entries":["This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it."]}],"_typeListText":["martial weapon","melee weapon"],"_typeHtml":"martial weapon (glaive), melee weapon","_attunement":"(requires attunement)","_attunementCategory":"Requires Attunement","_fProperties":["heavy","reach","two-handed"],"_fMisc":["Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBaseItem":["glaive|phb"],"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Martial weapon, melee weapon"}}}}}
{"_id":"mWeHXX7xAr6qqNzl","name":"Morning Star (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Morning_Star.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon, melee weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.dX8AxCh9o0A9CkT3]{Morningstar}), very rare (requires attunement)  </em><br /><em>4 lb.</em><br /><em>[[/r 1d8]] piercing</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Within these four, free-floating, ever-moving, gyroscopic rings is contained the source of <em>morning star</em>'s power: a ball of fusion; a miniaturised star. A creature attuned to the item can induce tiny solar flares that can blind or burn those in its path.</p>\n<p>You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. While attuned you can cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Bnn9Nzajixvow9xi]{Light} cantrip at will.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Dawn.</em></strong> As an action you can cause <em>morning star</em> to shine a gloriously bright light at all creatures within a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must succeed on a DC 16 Constitution saving throw or become blinded until the end of your next turn. One you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Ultraviolet.</em></strong> After you use the Dawn property, but before the next dawn, you can use an action to cause <em>morning star</em> to shine a focussed beam of ultraviolet light in a 5-foot-wide, 100-foot-long line. Each creature in the area must make a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 12d6]] radiant damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until you activate Dawn again.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Eclipse, Set of the Moon and Stars</h2>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\">When the magics of morning star and <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> become intertwined through attunement to a single wielder, their innate dunmantic magics coalesce creating a miniature solar system.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\">While you are attuned to both morning star and <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>, both items gain an additional +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, the saving throw DCs of both items are increased by 1 , and you can use the Orbit and Eclipse properties.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Orbit.</span></strong> Whenever you make a ranged attack with <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> while also holding morning star, you can use a bonus action to cause it to begin orbiting you. As part of this bonus action and as a bonus action on subsequent turns, you can make one attack with <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> against any creature within 15 feet of you.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Evening moon</span> orbits you at a distance of [[/r 1d3]] feet. Any creature within 5 feet of you can use its action to make a DC 21 Dexterity (Acrobatics) check in an attempt to catch <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>. On a success, the creature catches <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span>. On a failure, it takes [[/r 1d6]] slashing damage.</p>\n<p style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eclipse.</span></strong> As a bonus action while <span style=\"font-style:normal\">evening moon</span> is orbiting you, you can cause it to hover in front of you, casting you in a dark obscuring light. For the next minute you are under the effects of the blur spell. You must concentrate on Eclipse as if you were concentrating on a spell. After you activate this effect, you can’t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+1+@mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"nRsGy2d3iSNPmjyt","name":"Mechanical Tail (Uncommon)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Mechanical_Tail.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This item is another creation of the eccentric Anton Spark, tinkerer extraordinaire. This mechanical tail is powered by a magic-infused steam core. Any bipedal creature can wear it on its back and, once attuned, use it as if it was born with a tail.</p>\n<p>While attuned to the mechanical tail you can use it to grapple a target within reach. You have +2 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks you make to grapple a target with this tail.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Steam-powered Strike.</em></strong> As an action, you sweep your tail with wicked, steam-powered ferocity. Each creature within 5 feet of your must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 2d8]] slashing damage and be knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. Roll a [[/r d4]]; on a 1 the tail runs out of steam and can't be used again until you finish a short rest</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"5e Magic Items Vol. 0 Free For All","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Logo.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">Welcome to Loot Tavern’s FREE Foundry Item Compendium.</h2>\n<p><img src=\"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Banner.webp\" width=\"auto\" height=\"auto\" /></p>\n<p>Maximise your play time and wow your players with these drag-n-drop magic items! Art, stats, even new spells, it’s all ready for you! These items can also grow with your players, making storytelling arcs your group will never forget.</p>\n<p>45 pieces of art, 95 items (inc. rarity variants), on us.</p>\n<p>A little thank you to the wonderful Foundry community for your help!<br />Thanks 🙂</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Psst... We have a special offer.</p>\n<p>For the month of October, you can get ALL the themes we’ve done so far—that’s over 250 pieces of art and 500+ items (including rarity variants) for only <strong>$10</strong>.</p>\n<p>Save 92% on an MSRP of ~$140. Here’s how you do it:</p>\n<p>Head to <a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/join/LootTavern/checkout?rid=4819360\">our patreon</a> and back at the $10 tier. The link automatically chooses that tier for you.</p>\n<p>Head to <a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/inventory-all-38610375\"><em>The Inventory</em></a> and install the modules! Copy and paste the links from Patreon to the Manifest URL bar in the module browser. Press Install and...</p>\n<p><em>Volilà!</em>  You’re done!</p>\n</section>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":10,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RwDw2q9CYAeCNOaX"}},"_id":"oEVT2YxfjQhQYI26"}
{"_id":"oLww69UBNzRXvO95","name":"Glaive of the Green Tyrant (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glaive_of_the_Green_Tyrant.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.rOG1OM2ihgPjOvFW]{Glaive}), melee weapon, uncommon (requires attunement)</em> <br />6 lb.<br />[[/r 1d10]] slashing - heavy, reach, two-handed</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Legend tells of a great warrior queen who, having bested a bronze dragon in a game of wits, sought the ability to wield the power of storms. With this power, she laid waste to entire armies, throwing them back into the ranks of their allies, or burning them with flashes of incandescent lightning. Some called her liberator, others: tyrant. Though defeated by the Hero in Red, some of her power yet remains in the Green Tyrant's ancient glaive.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Summon Storm.</em></strong> With a flourish of the glaive you can expend a bonus action to whip up a tornado - 5-foot-diameter, 30-foot-high cylinder of rushing air and crackling lightning - centred on a point within 60 feet. The tornado lasts for 1 minute. Each creature that starts its turn in the tornado's space or enters the space for the first time on a turn must make a DC 13 Strength saving throw. On a failure, a creature is thrown 10 feet in a random direction, landing prone, and takes [[/r 1d4]] bludgeoning and [[/r 1d4]] lightning damage. Roll a [[/r d8]] to determine the direction: 1, north; 2, northeast; 3, east; 4, southeast; 5, south; 6, southwest; 7, west; or 8 northwest.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action on your turn while the tornado is conjured, you can move the tornado up to 20 feet. Each creature whose space the tornado moves through must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d4]] lightning damage. A creature can't take damage from this effect more than once per turn.</p>\n<p>Once you use the Summon Storm property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Heavy.</em></strong> Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Reach.</em></strong> This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Two-Handed.</em></strong> This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"hvy":true,"rch":true,"two":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"glaive%20of%20the%20green%20tyrant%20(uncommon)_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Glaive of the Green Tyrant (Uncommon)","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"fluff":{"images":[{"type":"image","href":{"type":"external","url":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Glaive_of_the_Green_Tyrant.webp"}}]