eld the power of storms. With this power, she laid waste to entire armies, throwing them back into the ranks of their allies, or burning them with flashes of incandescent lightning. Some called her liberator, others: tyrant. Though defeated by the Hero in Red, some of her power yet remains in the Green Tyrant's ancient glaive.",{"type":"entries","name":"Summon Storm","entries":["With a flourish of the glaive you can expend a bonus action to whip up a tornado - 5-foot-diameter, 30-foot-high cylinder of rushing air and crackling lightning - centred on a point within 60 feet. The tornado lasts for 1 minute. Each creature that starts its turn in the tornado's space or enters the space for the first time on a turn must make a DC 13 Strength saving throw. On a failure, a creature is thrown 10 feet in a random direction, landing {@condition prone}, and takes {@dice 1d4} bludgeoning and {@damage 1d4} lightning damage. Roll a {@dice d8} to determine the direction: 1, north; 2, northeast; 3, east; 4, southeast; 5, south; 6, southwest; 7, west; or 8 northwest.","As a bonus action on your turn while the tornado is conjured, you can move the tornado up to 20 feet. Each creature whose space the tornado moves through must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take {@damage 1d4} lightning damage. A creature can't take damage from this effect more than once per turn.","Once you use the Summon Storm property, you can't do so again until the following dawn."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Heavy","entries":["Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Reach","entries":["This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Two-Handed","entries":["This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it."]}],"_typeListText":["martial weapon","melee weapon"],"_typeHtml":"martial weapon (glaive), melee weapon","_attunement":"(requires attunement)","_attunementCategory":"Requires Attunement","_fProperties":["heavy","reach","two-handed"],"_fMisc":["Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBaseItem":["glaive|phb"],"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Martial weapon, melee weapon"}}}}}
{"_id":"pGwxzK8Ry8XlLHbC","name":"Owlsight Goggles","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Owlsight_Goggles.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, uncommo</em><em>n</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>You gain darkvisionout to a range of 60 feet and your ranged attacks do not suffer disadvantage when attacking at long range while standing in darkness.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Night Tracker.</em></strong> Once per long rest you may incite the goggles&rsquo; command word, activating their thermal vision. For the next 10 minutes, you can see all heat signatures within 20 feet. This includes items and objects warm-blooded creatures might have recently touched. This vision can penetrate through most barriers but is blocked by 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal or 3 feet of wood or dirt.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"none","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"lr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"q3GAQys8JFvsj0yM","name":"Magehunter Bulwark (Legendary)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Bulwark.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Armor (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.sSs3hSzkKBMNBgTs]{Shield}), legendary (requires attunement)</em><br />6 lb.<br />AC +2</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Like a leaden wall, spellbreakers would encircle evil magic users, sending spells ricocheting up into the night sky. Eventually, when the enemy's magic was spent, these red and black shields would thrust forwards, hammering their foe to the ground where they could be shackled. Though few are now found, these mage hunter bulwarks are a thorn in the side of even the mightiest Lich.</p>\n<p>While wielding and attuned to this magical shield, you gain a +2 bonus to your AC and gain the ‘Deflect Spell’ feature.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Deflect Spell.</em></strong> When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken, you can use your reaction to deflect some of the spell’s energy. When you do so, the damage you take from the attack/effect is reduced by [[/r 5d10]].</p>\n<p>If you reduce the damage to 0, the spell has no effect on you, and you can attempt to reflect the spell’s raw energy at its origin. Use the same spell slot level, spell save DC, attack bonus, and/or spellcasting ability of the caster/origin of the spell. On a hit or failed Dexterity saving throw, the target takes force damage equal to the damage absorbed.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, roll a [[/r d6]]. On a 1, the shield becomes overloaded and can’t deflect spells again until you finish a long rest.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":4,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qnI0mt1nj5Av2QxE","name":"Concubine's War Fan (Very Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Concubines_War_Fan.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Some assassins rely on stealth. Others, like the concubines of the Courteous Cabal, prefer to hide in plain sight, beguiling their quarry into a stupor before finishing them off with a quick slash.</p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-0d2a44c6-7fff-ca10-a8eb-69284e328458\">You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</span></p>\n<p><strong><em>Weapon.</em></strong>&nbsp;This magic fan can be used as a martial melee weapon. It has the finesse, light, and thrown (20/60 ft.) properties; and deals slashing damage equal to [[/r 1d6]] plus your ability modifier on a hit. Ranged weapon attacks made with this fan ignore half cover.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Beguiling Dance.</em></strong> As an action while holding the fan you can begin a slow, hypnotic dance, causing the fan to glow with an ephemeral, beguiling light. Each creature of your choice within 20 feet of you must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw contested by your Charisma (Performance) check or be charmed by you until you stop dancing. If you use your bonus action at the start of each turn to continue dancing, any charmed creatures remained charmed. The charm ends early if you're ever more than 20 feet from your target or if you or your companions do anything harmful to it. When the effect ends, the creature knows it was charmed by you. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Optional Attunement.</em></strong> While attuned to this fan you are proficient with it and you have advantage on Charisma (Performance) checks you make while holding this fan.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"+2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+@mod+2","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"mgc":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"r1U2cHO70nKMQNIU","name":"Magehunter Bulwark (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Bulwark.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Armor (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.sSs3hSzkKBMNBgTs]{Shield}), rare (requires attunement)</em><br />6 lb.<br />AC +2</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Like a leaden wall, spellbreakers would encircle evil magic users, sending spells ricocheting up into the night sky. Eventually, when the enemy's magic was spent, these red and black shields would thrust forwards, hammering their foe to the ground where they could be shackled. Though few are now found, these mage hunter bulwarks are a thorn in the side of even the mightiest Lich.</p>\n<p>While wielding and attuned to this magical shield, you gain a +1 bonus to your AC and gain the ‘Deflect Spell’ feature.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Deflect Spell.</em></strong> When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken, you can use your reaction to deflect some of the spell’s energy. When you do so, the damage you take from the attack/effect is reduced by [[/r 2d10]].</p>\n<p>If you reduce the damage to 0, the spell has no effect on you, and you can attempt to reflect the spell’s raw energy at its origin. Use the same spell slot level, spell save DC, attack bonus, and/or spellcasting ability of the caster/origin of the spell. On a hit or failed Dexterity saving throw, the target takes force damage equal to the damage absorbed.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, roll a [[/r d6]]. On a 1, the shield becomes overloaded and can’t deflect spells again until you finish a long rest.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d10",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":3,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rM5tQUIYb06NKDlQ","name":"Arclight Rapier (Uncommon)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Arclight_Rapier.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier}), uncommon <br />Martial weapon, melee weapon <br />2 lb.<br />[[/r 1d8]] piercing - finesse</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A tool-weapon inspired by the Clockwork Nirvana, a plane of precise law and order, this blade is equally capable of repairing mechanical marvels or incapacitating malfunctioning automatons. On the Material Plane, such weapons are carried by tech-priests, holy clerics whose altar is a workbench and whose sermon is the clang of a hammer on an anvil.</p>\n<p>This magic weapon has 8 charges and regains [[/r 1d6 + 2]] charges daily at dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Arclight Weld.</em></strong> When you hit a target with a weapon attack using this weapon you can pull a concealed trigger to expend a charge and cause a flash of lightning to burst from your weapon. The target takes an additional [[/r 1d4]] lightning damage. In addition, if the target is made of non-magical metal or is a creature wearing non-magical metal armour, it must succeed on a DC 13 Strength saving throw or have the metal become welded. While wearing welded armour, or while its body is welded, the creature gains the welded condition: its speed is reduced by 10 feet for each welded stack it has accumulated.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Unwelding.</em></strong> All stacks of the welded condition can be ended in one of two ways: brute force or delicate tinkering.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Brute Force. A welded creature can use its action to make a DC 13 Strength check. On a success, it removes the welded condition but damages the metal, gaining a permanent -1 to its AC while it wears the armour, until the armour is repaired. On a failure, nothing happens.</li>\n<li>Tinkering. A creature can spend 10 minutes to make a DC 13 Dexterity (smith's or tinkerer's tools)* check. On a success, it ends the welded condition. On a failure, it ends the welded condition but damages the metal, conferring a permanent -1 to its AC while it wears the armour, until the armour is repaired.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":8,"max":"8","per":"charges"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","piercing"],["1d4","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"mgc":true,"ada":false,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true,"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rWjKrLz72TJONuZa","name":"Mechanical Tail (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Mechanical_Tail.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This item is another creation of the eccentric Anton Spark, tinkerer extraordinaire. This mechanical tail is powered by a magic-infused steam core. Any bipedal creature can wear it on its back and, once attuned, use it as if it was born with a tail.</p>\n<p>While attuned to the mechanical tail you can use it to grapple a target within reach. You have +4 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks you make to grapple a target with this tail.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Steam-powered Strike.</em></strong> As an action, you sweep your tail with wicked, steam-powered ferocity. Each creature within 5 feet of your must succeed on a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 4d8]] slashing damage and be knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. Roll a [[/r d4]]; on a 1 the tail runs out of steam and can't be used again until you finish a short rest</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d8","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rjYhCCLhjSHtYWno","name":"Demonic Siege Bow","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Demonic_Siege_Bow.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>What this weapon lacks in maneuverability it makes up for in power. Wrought from the horns, bones, and sinew of demons this magic weapon holds malice in every fibre. With its very own bracing mechanism, a user can free up a hand to fire using both strings at once.</p>\n<p>A Strength score of 13 or higher is required to use this weapon. The damage die of this weapon is increased by one step (i.e. a longbow becomes a d10, a shortbow a d8).</p>\n<p><strong><em>Siege Brace.</em></strong> As an action, you speak the bow’s command word causing a skeletal, demonic hand to burst from the ground and hold the bow steady until you use an action to dismiss it. The bow can’t be moved while grasped by the skeletal hand; a successful DC 13 Strength check is required to wrest it from this grasp. While in this ‘siege mode’, each time you make a ranged weapon attack using this bow you can make one additional attack against the same target (no action required). When you do so, both attacks are made with disadvantage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>SoarBones.</em></strong> You can use this weapon to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.wpx42mtoZ5BmXRs1]{Phantom Steed} spell at will. The weapon grows skeletal wings and feet, turning into a vicious looking crow named SoarBones. In addition to the steed's normal statistics, it has a fly speed equal to its walking speed.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.3cymOVja8jXbzrdT]{Longbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.yaLtkM5AAFkSlF48]{Demonic Siege Bow (Longbow)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.GJv6WkD7D2J6rP6M]{Shortbow} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.czqcwb4KJWHRDkU8]{Demonic Siege Bow (Shortbow)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"items.html","source":"LooTavern","hash":"demonic%20siege%20bow_lootavern","data":{"item":{"name":"Demonic Siege Bow","type":"GV","requires":[{"bow":true}],"inherits":{"namePrefix":"Demonic Siege Bow (","nameSuffix":")","source":"LooTavern","page":0,"rarity":"uncommon","reqAttune":true,"entries":["What this weapon lacks in maneuverability it makes up for in power. Wrought from the horns, bones, and sinew of demons this magic weapon holds malice in every fibre. With its very own bracing mechanism, a user can free up a hand to fire using both strings at once.","A Strength score of 13 or higher is required to use this weapon. The damage die of this weapon is increased by one step (i.e. a longbow becomes a d10, a shortbow a d8).",{"type":"entries","name":"Siege Brace","entries":["As an action, you speak the bow’s command word causing a skeletal, demonic hand to burst from the ground and hold the bow steady until you use an action to dismiss it. The bow can’t be moved while grasped by the skeletal hand; a successful DC 13 Strength check is required to wrest it from this grasp. While in this ‘siege mode’, each time you make a ranged weapon attack using this bow you can make one additional attack against the same target (no action required). When you do so, both attacks are made with disadvantage."]},{"type":"entries","name":"SoarBones","entries":["You can use this weapon to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.wpx42mtoZ5BmXRs1]{Phantom Steed} spell at will. The weapon grows skeletal wings and feet, turning into a vicious looking crow named SoarBones. In addition to the steed's normal statistics, it has a fly speed equal to its w