{"_id":"s3D1H3IeDep8jBS2","name":"Purple Wyrmfist (Very Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Purple_Wyrmfist.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tWondrous item, very rare (requires attunement)\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t  \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<hr />\n\t\t<p>From the striking violet chitin of the subterranean purple worm is crafted this surprisingly tactile gauntlet. Each day, the gauntlet produces a diluted version of the worm's toxin that is able to cause debilitating pain through a single touch. Purple worm chitin is a sound enhancer, able to amplify vibrations and grant its wearer the ability to detect the slightest tremor.</p><p><strong><em>Purple Poison.</em></strong> As a bonus action you can cause the gauntlet to secrete a purple worm toxin. The next time you hit a creature with an unarmed strike, or successfully grapple a creature, the creature must make a DC 16 Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 8d6]] poison damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. After you activate this property, roll a [[/r d8]]. On a 1 or 2 you can't activate this property again until the following dawn.</p><p><strong><em>Tactile Touch.</em></strong> As an action you can touch the ground with this gauntlet and gain tremorsense out to a radius of 60 feet for as long as you remain in contact with the ground.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":"you successfully hit or grapple a creature with an unarmed strike"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","poison"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":16,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"t9nSOFVRIpgUz0nq","name":"Rapier of the Yellow King","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Rapier_of_the_Yellow_King.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier}), melee weapon, legendary (requires attunement)</em><br />2 lb.</p>\n<p>[[/r 1d8]] piercing - finesse</p>\n<hr />\n<p>The guard of this slender, sickly, yellow blade houses a snake’s eye that seems to follow its quarry around the room when drawn. Gifted by hags who served the King in Yellow this trinket contains powers of mind control and hexing.</p>\n<p>You have +2 bonus to attack damage rolls made with this weapon. When you hit with it, the target an additional [[/r 2d6]] psychic damage. You gain the following benefits while you hold this rapier:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can speak deep speech fluently.</li>\n<li>You can cast @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.91Sw6vOIaO7U8DvM]{Dominate Person}(save DC 17). Once you have done so, you can’t use it this way again until the following dawn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Shackles of Pain.</em></strong> As a bonus action, you can choose one creature you can see within 60 feet. That creature must succeed on a DC 17 Charisma saving throw or become cursed and bound to you for the next minute. Whenever you take damage from any source, the other creature takes half as much damage of the same type so long as it is on the same plane of existence as you. This effect can be removed by any spell or effect that removes hexes or curses. Once you use this feature, you can’t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Finesse.</em></strong> When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"2","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+2+@mod","piercing"],["2d6","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"fin":true,"amm":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ugKgC6bxSUz2UZF8","name":"Trident of the Electric Eel (Rare)","type":"weapon","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Trident_of_the_Electric_Eel.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.F65ANO66ckP8FDMa]{Trident}), melee weapon, rare (requires attunement)</em><br />4 lb.<br />[[/r 1d6]] piercing - thrown (20/60 ft.), versatile ([[/r 1d8]])</p>\n<hr />\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Imbued with the natural lightning-based magic of the eelfolk, this brass-headed, magical trident is enchanted never to succumb to the corrosive nature of the briny sea.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><em>Discharge.</em></strong> When you make a melee or ranged attack using this magic weapon you can speak its command word as a bonus action, causing it to emit a burst of lightning. Each creature within 5 feet of it (or within 10 feet of it underwater), must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d10]] lightning damage. A creature that fails this saving throw by 10 or more (DC 3) is also stunned until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Dinglehopper.</strong></em> As an action, you can command this weapon to magically shrink down to the size of common oyster folk, known as a dinglehopper, or to re-enlarge.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Lightning.</strong></em> As an action, you can cast the spell @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.IyikgTEOTv701jgQ]{Lightning Bolt} (save DC 15) at 5th level. Once you do so, you can&rsquo;t use the Discharge or Lightning feature again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":true,"ada":false,"mgc":false,"sil":false},"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":null,"path":"itemss","color":"#ae8989"}}}
{"_id":"yGnwS3ixTUFkiyUW","name":"Venus Fools Trap","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Venus_fools_Trap.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This cloak is made from a shapeshifting sub species of carnivorous plants. Unnatural magic is involved in the alterations necessary to transform a living creature into a garment. Yet the metamorphosis is far from perfect, and this cloak hungers for flesh. When worn, you can feel the cloak pulsing and moving around your body.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Lunch break.</em></strong> As an action, you can put the cloak on a flat non magical surface. It adapts to the surface and matches its properties. The cloak covers a surface 10 feet long and 5 feet wide. If a creature uses its action to examine the area the cloak is in, the creature can spot the hidden carnivorous item with a successful DC 17 Wisdom (Perception) check. If a creature enters the space occupied by the cloak, it must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 2d10+8]] piercing damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p> <p><strong><em>Take-out.</em></strong> When a creature enters a space within 10 feet of you, you can use your reaction to have the cloak pounce and wrap around the creature. The creature must succeed a DC15 Strength saving throw or be @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.b4UvTt9P3As79cwm]{Grappled}by the carnivorous cloak. While grappled in this way, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained}and takes [[/r 2d8+4]] acid damage at the end of each of its turns. A creature restrained by the cloak can use its action to make a DC15 Strength check, freeing itself on a success. When a creature frees itself, the cloak falls to the ground and moves 10 feet closer to you at the start of each of your turns, until it reaches you. This property can't be used again until you finish a short or long rest.</p> <p><strong><em>Take-out.</em></strong> This cloak is cursed, a fact that is revealed only when you attune to it. Attuning to it curses you until you are targeted by the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.XZhdgVK3cLoxNCQl]{Remove Curse}spell or similar magic; removing the cloak fails to end the curse and it always seems to find its way back to you at the end of a long rest. While cursed, the cloak must feast on the corpse of at least a small creature every 24 hours. Failing to do so, causes it to slowly digest you during a long rest. When you finish a long rest, you recover one less hit dice, and take [[/r 2d6]] acid damage upon waking up.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d10+8","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"n6xwikFD7X7aWF9l":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"yWQoktA5tfLnYN6r","name":"Coolmint Slice (Very Rare)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sugar_Shivs.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, very rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This striped, blue blade is enchanted with the power of the elemental coolmint. You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Decorate.</em></strong> While holding this weapon, you can use your action to conjure a torrent of sticky, white and purple sugar as you cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.RpKjTlYASrfqUPVA]{Cone of Cold} spell (save DC 16). Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Magic Item Set.</em></strong> Attuning to both this weapon and the peppermint slice requires only a single attunement slot. If you hit a creature with both of these weapons on the same turn, the weapons become empowered until the end of your next turn. This weapon deals an additional [[/r 1d8]] cold damage and the peppermint slice deals an additional [[/r 1d8]] fire damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.0ec0h2VijJQvmfHI]{Coolmint Slice (Dagger) (Very Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.ULIdjLgTGPPORRcP]{Coolmint Slice (Scimitar) (Very Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"yb9473Enw81svJXv","name":"Purple Wyrmfist (Rare)","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Purple_Wyrmfist.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</p>\n<hr />\n<p>From the striking violet chitin of the subterranean purple worm is crafted this surprisingly tactile gauntlet. Each day, the gauntlet produces a diluted version of the worm's toxin that is able to cause debilitating pain through a single touch. Purple worm chitin is a sound enhancer, able to amplify vibrations and grant its wearer the ability to detect the slightest tremor.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Purple Poison.</em></strong> As a bonus action you can cause the gauntlet to secrete a purple worm toxin. The next time you hit a creature with an unarmed strike, or successfully grapple a creature, the creature must make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 6d6]] poison damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. After you activate this property, roll a [[/r d6]]. On a 1 or 2 you can't activate this property again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Tactile Touch.</em></strong> As an action you can touch the ground with this gauntlet and gain @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.MzNASNCgB0Qi2m8p]{Tremorsense} out to a radius of 30 feet for as long as you remain in contact with the ground.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":"you successfully hit or grapple a creature with an unarmed strike"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d6","poison"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"yqDIytWZY6Ao6tx3","name":"Broodmother's Eye","type":"equipment","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Broodmothers_Eye.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tWondrous item, common (requires attunement)\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t  \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<hr />\n\t\t<p>While socketed in an attuneable magic item, the item gains the ‘Intense Stare' property.</p><p><strong><em>Intense Stare.</em></strong> The socketed aboleth's eye fixes on a humanoid that you can see within 60 feet of you that isn't hostile towards you, making you seem both alluring and imposing. For the next minute, you have advantage on all Charisma (Persuasion and Intimidation) checks made to interact with the creature. After this minute elapses, the creature realizes that you used magic to influence its mood. How it reacts is at the GM's discretion. Once you use this property, you can't do so again until the following dawn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":1,"equipped":true,"rarity":"common","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":null,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zuDp4y8G6f1gKQnA","name":"Coolmint Slice (Uncommon)","type":"loot","img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sugar_Shivs.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This striped, blue blade is enchanted with the power of the elemental coolmint. You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Glaze.</em></strong> While holding this weapon, you can use your action to conjure a torrent of sticky, white and purple sugar as you cast the @Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.magic-items.XX2v3qBfUo8vi9oQ]{Cone of Frosting} spell (save DC 13). Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Magic Item Set.</em></strong> Attuning to both this weapon and the peppermint slice requires only a single attunement slot. If you hit a creature with both of these weapons on the same turn, the weapons become empowered until the end of your next turn. This weapon deals an additional [[/r 1d4]] cold damage and the peppermint slice deals an additional [[/r 1d4]] fire damage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.0E565kQUBmndJ1a2]{Dagger} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.ibufaw4ELK7vxFbT]{Coolmint Slice (Dagger) (Uncommon)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.variant-items.0quzYIecuGQhmgp6]{Coolmint Slice (Scimitar) (Uncommon)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"uncommon","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xzzTW4YMhGKM0emi":3},"flags":{}}
